d[37022]={de="The wolves of Draenor are some of the most savage beasts around, but they've also gotten used to the sights and smells of the orcs and ogres that live here. It shouldn't take us much time at all to train this little ball of fur and death. Let's set it loose against the ogres of the region that yer familiar with. That Gorian Beast-Lasher, the one that smells of blood and fear, go on and see how your wolf reacts to that."}
d[37023]={de="The windrocs of Nagrand are a smart predator, often swooping down on unwary prey in packs. If your beast doesn't keep an eye on the sky, it's likely to lose both of em.' Head on out to Nagrand and take on the fiercest windroc of the bunch, the Darkwing Roc. That'll be a good test for the both of ye."}
d[37024]={de="Deep in the forests of Nagrand are some beasts capable of evading almost any predator. The greatest of them all, the Moth of Wrath, is coated with a foul-smelling dust. If the moth dust is enough to keep wolves at bay, it'll probably be a pretty good test for your wolf. See if you can't keep it focused and take down that moth."}
d[37025]={de="The elements can sometimes pose a problem for some beasts. Ever seen a ram in a thunderstorm? They'll hide behind anything larger than themselves. I'm not sure if they think the world is ending or what, but it's not great if you're atop one at the time. In Nagrand, off on a windswept cliff high above the shore, is a creature made of pure thunderstorms. Hop atop your wolf and face off against Thundercall, and we'll see if it gets spooked."}
