d[37028]={de="I've got one last challenge for ye, commander, but if it isn't a doozy. They call them the garn. Wolves as black as night, and twice the size of a normal wolf, they can tear a man apart in seconds. Any beast in their right mind would be scared witless at the sight of such a predator. There's a lone garn that's made it from their usual home in Frostfire, all the way over to Nagrand. Take your wolf, mount up, and bring it down. If the two of you survive, your wolf will truly be ready."}
d[37125]={de="Every once in a while an archaeologist experiences a rare find... an artifact that time has delicately preserved through the ages, as if it had simply fallen out of a time machine. Even thinking about the thrill of such a find makes me get all emotional... relics like that are worth a freakin' fortune!"}
d[37145]={de="Listen, I don't know how I got here, but I have it on good authority that there is an entire island made of shiny things and it's just off of the coast a ways. All we have to do is hop in the water and swim out there, then we can load up our pockets and swim back! I'm just going to rest up and do some stretching before heading out. Don't try and stop me!"}
d[37149]={de="My 'master' is an idiot, but you look like you've got some smarts in that oddly-shaped head. Listen up, the Twisting Nether is a chaotic abyss, and things work differently there. I've felt some disturbances, and they don't bode well for any of us. Yes, there are things happening here, in Draenor, that are causing ripples in the nether. No, don't try to wrap your head around how that works, you'll only hurt yourself. It's simple: bring me a Void-Gate Key, and maybe I can stop the bad things."}
d[37203]={de="I don't really like when my pets fight, but I love making them feel better when they're done."}
d[37210]={de="Aogexon is one of the most feared beasts in Nagrand, and one of the largest and most dangerous forest stalkers ever seen! I've already been approached by a number of a collectors interested in obtaining one of Aogexon's deadly fangs. If you are up for the challenge, Aogexon can sometimes be found lurking in the swamp not far from here. Good luck!"}
d[37211]={de="An anonymous collector of valuable fossils and antiques has offered the preservation society a huge cash reward for Bergruu's horn. A huge reward, {name}... HUGE!"}
d[37221]={de="Few elekk have lived as long as Dekorhan. Elekk tusks continue to grow throughout the elekk's lifetime. This makes Dekorhan's tusks some of the largest and oldest on Draenor. Do you hear what I hear, {name}? That's the sound of all the gold jingling in our pockets after you bring me Dekorhan's tusk!"}
d[37222]={de="Most talbuk are peaceful creatures that will only attack when they are defending their herd. Not Direhoof though, that talbuk is one of the most aggresively dangerous beasts I've ever encountered... and one of the most magnificent talbuk I've ever seen! If you encounter Direhoof while adventuring and live to tell the tale, return to me with the beast's hide and I'll see that you're rewarded!"}
d[37223]={de="Deep in the forest of northern Nagrand is a giant Gronn known as Gagrog the Brutal. In case you're wondering, he didn't get his name by giving out free hugs... this Gronn is as savage and murderous as they come! Now look, I'm not telling you to go try and hunt this thing down... that would be suicide... but if by some miracle you fight Gagrog and live, make sure you bring back his skull!"}
d[37224]={de="Not far from here is a hippo of unusual size and ferocity known as Mu'gra. I've been contacted by a private collector that would like to acquire Mu'gra's teeth for a special exhibit. Hippo teeth are extremely difficult to extract, and we can't be selling damaged goods so just bring back the entire head, got it? Good luck!"}
d[37225]={de="Windrocs can be found all over Nagrand, from the highest peaks to the lowest valleys. However, one windroc in particular is extremely elusive and is rarely sighted, it is known to the orcs as Thek'talon. If I know anything, it's that people will pay a lot of money for anything that is rare or elusive!"}
d[37226]={de="Xelganak is as deadly as they come, {name}! I don't recommend going after Xelganak unless you love money, adventure, and glory. Xelganak's poison stinger would be an easy sell to the right collector, so if you're up for the challenge I'll make sure you get handsomely rewarded. Just don't go getting your face melted off like Bozzil, ok?"}
d[37230]={de="Welcome back, commander. The commander is obviously in a great hurry, and certainly the thought of removing their coat or boots or not dripping all over the floor are much too far beyond consideration. The commander remembers the acidic solution, yes? Quite effective it was, though one barrel was not enough to remove ALL of the blood stains from the portraits, or the tapestries, or the ceiling. Surely this must have been the most heroic and viscous battle in recent history."}
d[37231]={de="An old deckhand inspected that device you brought us, and thinks it was quite the forgery. This Iron Horde is trying to copy the mechanism, but they don't quite have the technology. When you get right down to it, we're not sure how these primitive beasts got a hold of this kind of tool. Wouldn't be half as good of a sea tale if we knew, ha! We've still got a pile of treasure with your name on it, if you can find us the real compass."}
d[37238]={de="We have reviewed Ner'zhul's notes, which you brought to us previously. Though we are closer to understanding how these warlocks have learned to bind souls and control the undead, the picture is incomplete. We will need more pages if we are to see the whole picture. I do not want to experiment with partial information and create an abomination. There are enough of those in Northrend as it is."}
d[37239]={de="I feel that I can trust you, perhaps. You have, at least, not spoken of my secret to anyone, and for that I thank you. I have need of your aid again, and in return, I will share some of my own information. I am here, you see, to find an elf by the name of Alleria. She was lost years ago, on Draenor. It is my faint hope that the twisting nether brought her here. I do not know if such a thing is even possible, but do keep an eye out for any signs of high elves as you travel."}
d[37520]={de="Vileclaw is feared throughout Nagrand as a vicious predator. While it is true that Vileclaw is one of the most dangerous raptors you'll ever encounter, she is also a savagely beautiful creature. Vileclaw must be preserved for future generations to behold! If you can bring me back one of her vicious claws, I'll make sure you get a cut of the profit!"}
d[37523]={de="The ogres at the Gorian Proving Grounds are rousing champions to turn against our forces in Nagrand. A decisive assault on their training grounds should prevent them from mustering the forces they need to stand against us, and will help remind them that we are not an enemy they want to make."}
d[37524]={de="The ogres at the Gorian Proving Grounds be rousin' champions to turn against our forces in Nagrand. A decisive assault on their training grounds should prevent dem from musterin' the forces dey be needin' to stand against us, and will help remind them that we are not an enemy they want to be makin'."}
d[37783]={de="The Iron Docks is one of the Iron Horde's greatest assets in this war. Our scouts have reported that the docks are alight with activity, indicating imminent attack. Skulloc, son of Gruul, was seen leaving the Blackrock Foundry, armed to the teeth with powerful cannons, and has been loaded onto their mightiest warship. It does not matter where they intend to strike, commander - you must sack the Iron Docks and defeat Skulloc before they ever leave."}
d[37784]={de="Ner'zhul was once a noble orc - he was the wise chieftain and elder shaman of the Shadowmoon clan. In his desperate bid to join the Iron Horde he has spat on all he once stood for and twisted his ancestors' spirits to tap into dark, forbidden power... all to please Hellscream. The Shadowmoon has fallen, commander. Enter their ancestral burial grounds and put an end to Ner'zhul's madness before he pulls all of Draenor into the engulfing maw of the void."}
d[37788]={de="In Nagrand, the ogres tell of an ancient weapon called Gutrek's cleaver. I would very much like to study it. A goblin treasure hunter by the name of Val Goldspade discovered the whereabouts of the weapon. Unfortunately, this goblin has gone missing somewhere in the Broken Precipice - probably after a run-in with the locals."}
d[37797]={de="The journal points to the location of the pieces of Gutrek's Cleaver. It reads: \"The pommel was brought to the Broken Precipice, where it was to be housed in the skull of Gutrek's first kill. It looks like it was some manner of large beast that he fought in the big bone pit.\""}
d[37798]={de="The search for Gutrek's Cleaver continues. The journal reads: \"The hilt was to be buried in the marshlands, among the serpents whose poison claimed Gutrek's life. There's something here about covering it with a spiral stone, which is supposed to keep Gutrek's spirit at bay somehow.\""}
d[37799]={de="Only one piece remains. The journal reads: \"The final piece, Gutrek's blade, was to be displayed in a place of honor for all time overlooking the Ring of Blood. I don't think I've seen it there myself, but it says it's supposed to be somewhere where it has a clear view of every battle.\""}
d[37811]={de="With the pieces recovered, all that is left is to reforge Gutrek's Cleaver. Goldspade's journal seems to indicate that the only place to do this is the location where it was initially dismantled. The journal mentions a \"Spirit Forge\" used to dismantle the blade, and that it may be located somewhere in the nearby gorge. Find the forge and use it to combine the pieces you've gathered."}
d[37868]={de="You like this big race, do you? Me too! It has four legs: get to the purple post, then green, then red, then back here. Your time matters, so do it fast!"}
d[37881]={de="In Shadowmoon Valley there is a cave said to possess an ancient tome that may contain secrets that can help our cause against the Iron Horde. The cave, however, is protected by an ancient barrier composed of arcane energy. There is a goblin in Darktide Roost, said to know how to take down any barrier. Persuade him to give up his secrets and bring back the book."}
d[37882]={de="You will need three ingredients to make Megacharge's special \"Arcane Bunker Buster,\" which should be able to take down the barrier. The first ingredient, some precision blasting powder, should be available nearby. The book reads: \"To make one, you'll first need to acquire some high grade, precision blasting powder. Here in Blackfuse Company, it's pretty easy to come by, since they use it for all of the cannons.\""}
d[37883]={de="With the blasting powder acquired, you now must find a suitable detonator. A note attached to the entry in the cookbook hints to where one might be found: \"Reminder: Order more high-voltage detonators. The last shipment was lost off of the Shadowmoon coast near the demon-inhabited cliffs. Maybe we should send a diving team to salvage.\""}
d[37884]={de="The final ingredient to create Megacharge's bomb is a sizable quantity of demon's blood. Unfortunately, that's not something they're likely to give up easily..."}
d[37885]={de="The components have been gathered and the \"Arcane Bunker Buster\" is assembled. Hopefully, this should pack enough punch to take out the barrier. There's only one way to find out..."}
d[37910]={de="Ok, Darkmoon Racer, let's see what you got! The real race has four legs: get to the blue post, then green, then red, then back here. Your time matters, so do it fast!"}
d[37911]={de="Here's the big one! Good luck out there! This race has four legs: get to the purple post, then green, then red, then back here. Your time matters, so do it fast!"}
d[37914]={de="In Frostfire Ridge, a Thunderlord sage by the name of Argoram seems to have uncovered the whereabouts of a storied weapon, known to the orcs as Gronnsbane. He was last spotted headed into Magnarok. Find him and see if he can lead you to this relic."}
d[37916]={de="Looking through Argoram's journal, it becomes apparent that claiming this relic will be far more complicated than simply finding the pieces of the spear. However, that would be the best place to start..."}
d[37917]={de="The weapon has been assembled, but it lacks the power that made it a legend. In order to restore it, you must receive three blessings: one of fire, one of frost, and one of beasts. The first blessing mentioned in the journal is that of fire. The journal reads: \"He describes an ancient monolith, perched upon the edge of a precipice extending from the cliff where the searing magma falls into the sea. I believe the location he speaks of is just overlooking Tor'goroth's Tooth.\""}
d[37918]={de="The weapon has been imbued with the Blessing of Fire, drawing power from the Molten Shamanstone. The Frozen Shamanstone should impart the next blessing. Argoram mentions its location in his journal: \"As I was maneuvering away from the great boulders hurled at me by the ogron brutes, I glanced what looked like another monolith atop the tallest of the snow-capped towers in Bloodmaul. Perhaps this is the Frozen Shamanstone, which is thought to grant the Blessing of Frost\""}
d[37919]={de="Gronnsbane now pulses with energies of fire and frost. All that remains to restore the full power of the weapon is to receive the Blessing of the Beast. Argoram believed this could be accomplished by bloodying the weapon against one of the ancient black rylaks of Stonefury Cliffs. His journal reads: \"High in the Stonefury Cliffs, I have seen an altar where the ogres have left offerings to these ancient beasts. Perhaps I could use it to lure one of them\""}
d[37940]={de="The Iron Horde continues to bring in reinforcements from all over Draenor to reinforce their position at Hellfire Citadel. If we don't cut off the flow of supplies then we risk losing control of our plans in Tanaan. A strategic attack to the supply lines at Ironhold Harbor is just the thing to keep the Iron Horde on the defensive and maintain our momentum."}
d[37968]={de="Up in the hills of Tanaan Jungle, the Sargerei have converted a once-sacred temple into a den of demonic summoning. We must attack them now, before their rituals complete. The longer we delay, the stronger our enemy grows."}
d[37973]={de="I have heard of a draenei artificer by the name of Maatun that was seeking to restore an old draenei crystal, possibly of naaru origin. He called the crystal the Dream of Argus. The draenei went missing after seeking out help from the Shadowmoon orcs back before they allied themselves with the Iron Horde. One of your scouts recently spotted a draenei matching the description of Maatun near the entrance of the Pillars of Fate. Go there and see what you can dig up."}
d[37976]={de="In his quest to restore the Dream of Argus, Maatun enlisted the help of three orcs. These same orcs betrayed him and took the crystal shards before they could be combined. If you find these orcs, they may still have them. The first target shouldn't be far. The journal reads: \"I was told she spent most of her time in the crystal cave to the north of the encampment. There she studied the native crystals for ways to improve their potential abilities.\""}
d[37977]={de="The second orc that Matuun mentioned was a master runecarver and sorcerer. He should be located somewhere in the main camp. The journal reads: \"She mentioned that the orc could normally found in one of the runemaster's huts in the southern part of the camp. They could be identified by the standing stones surrounding the structure, as well as the floating runestones above.\""}
d[37978]={de="The last orc to be found was a hermit who kept away from the bulk of the Shadowmoon orcs at the Pillars of Fate camp, but was often seen in the high hills above. The journal reads: \"It is said, however, that he can often be seen among the graves upon the high hill, overlooking the camp below. There he would commune with the dead ancestors, whom it is said he preferred over his living brethren.\""}
d[37979]={de="With the shards recovered, it is now possible to restore the Dream of Argus. You must seek out the device that Maatun mentions in his journal, which is said to be in a cave overlooking Anguish Fortress."}
d[38044]={de="The Bleeding Hollow provide significant reinforcement to the Iron Horde in Tanaan. From their home in Zeth'Gol they relentlessly pursue our scouts, disrupt our operations, and gather more power for Gul'dan's magic. We should consider a direct raid on Zeth'Gol to make them pull back their forces across the valley. This should give us some breathing room... for a time."}
d[38046]={de="General, our troops are currently engaged in a conjoined assault at the Iron Front. The fight has been raging for some time now, and casualties are high. Report to the Iron Front and lend your strength to the war effort. I have no doubt that your presence on the battlefield will inspire the soldiers to victory!"}
d[38175]={de="We've had a breakthrough in melting down the scraps you've been collecting! If you can get me a small pile of 'em, we can get your troops something a bit more useful."}
d[38243]={de="Ore has been in high demand on my trading route, and I'm trying to restock my supply. Would you be willing to trade?"}
d[38250]={de="The Shadow Council have recruited the Sethekk and other power hungry Arakkoa to their service. Our allies in the Order of the Awakened have tracked them to a ruin in the west of Tanaan where the Shadow Council is instructing them in the use of fel magic. We must strike at them before they can master their diabolic powers."}
d[38287]={de="Raw beast hide has been in high demand on my trading route, and I'm trying to restock my supply. Would you be willing to trade?"}
d[38293]={de="Sumptuous fur has been in high demand on my trading route, and I'm trying to restock my supply. Would you be willing to trade?"}
d[38296]={de="Herbs have been in high demand on my trading route, and I'm trying to restock my supply. Would you be willing to trade?"}
d[38399]={de="Looking to sell something?"}
d[38440]={de="The Iron Horde is growing stronger each day as their war machines are empowered with fel magic. We have even obtained word that they are constructing a Fel Reaver! Head to the Fel Forge and destroy their forces before we are overwhelmed."}
d[38586]={de="The Shadow Council are summoning their demonic masters upon a mountain they are calling the Throne of Kil'jaeden. Make no mistake; This is the most dangerous region in Tanaan. Gather together a war party and assault the Throne of Kil'jaeden before the Legion gains a foothold here!"}
d[39433]={de="The corruption in the Apexis has begun to affect many of my people. We are so accustomed to the power it grants us that more succumb to the whispers every day. You must bring me more samples so I can free my people from yet another curse."}
d[39509]={de="Them Bleeding Hollow orcs do blood magic - like voodoo but it hurt more. They cut their own flesh. Most of 'em carry curved ritual blades for carvin' themselves up. Bring me them blades, commander. We can turn their power against 'em."}
d[39510]={de="What be left of the Iron Horde is comin' to Tanaan through Ironhold Harbor. If we knew who was comin' and when, we could use our shipyard to cause some chaos. Go to Ironhold Harbor and fish up some intelligence!"}
d[39511]={de="Orcs that drink Gul'dan's poison turn into fel beasts. Soulless savages. Lady Liadrin an' the Blood Knights think maybe there be a way back. They be wantin' samples of blood from freshly turned orcs. Get their blood, {name}! You be findin' fel orcs all over Tanaan, but the Iron Front, the Fel Forge, and the Throne of Kil'jaeden is where you find the most."}
d[39512]={de="Gul'dan be growin' his Shadow Council like a spider spin a web. But some of this new blood, they not so smart. They write down the secrets but don't burn 'em. Catch his minions out in the open and bring their secrets back to me! You find them workin' with the arakkoa in da Ruins of Kra'nak or atop the Throne of Kil'jaeden."}
d[39513]={de="Draenei at the Temple of Sha'naar would mine these mountains for perfect crystals used to channel their magics. Now demons be lootin' the place. We gotta keep those crystals out of demonic hands, commander! Attack the mines behind the temple and grab them crystals."}
d[39519]={de="Look to the north, {class}. The sky is turning a sickly green. Gul'dan's summoning portals are not yet at full strength, but already the stench of demon is on the wind. Slay them, {name}. Destroy as many beasts as you can before they find a way to Azeroth. The Temple of Sha'naar is infested, as is the Throne of Kil'jaeden, although you may find others wandering about the jungle."}
d[39526]={de="We got Gul'dan's minions on the run, commander! If you be feelin' it, we should put some pressure on some of his other strongholds as well."}
d[39529]={de="Beyond the meager shelter of these fortress walls, the jungle closes in. Can you feel it? That is the untamed wilderness, {class}, calling forth our primal instincts. There is no better way to feel alive than to court death. Join me in the hunt, {name}! Collect teeth from the wild beasts. The ravagers in Thornmire, the raptors in Zorammarsh - even the sea creatures along the strand and the little podling plants themselves all have teeth. Bring them to me!"}
d[39532]={de="Ever since the fall of Blackrock Foundry, Gul'dan has been turning the Iron Horde into... something worse. The orcs who once flocked to Grommash's banner, through either fear or thirst for revenge, are now embracing the fel. Wade into the battlefields of Tanaan and lay waste to Gul'dan's forces. Orc or fel orc makes no difference. Gut what remains of the Iron Horde!"}
d[39569]={de="Gul'dan's fel poison turns already ferocious orcs into hateful, vicious creatures with no soul. But were he here to guide us, Prophet Velen wouldn't give up on the whole race. If you could find samples of their blood, maybe we can reverse the process? You'll find fel orcs all over Tanaan, but the Iron Front, the Fel Forge, and the Throne of Kil'jaeden are the most densely populated."}
d[39573]={de="We have always believed that the primal creatures of Draenor could not be tamed. And yet, the Iron Horde found a way to weaponize the gronn. It would be to our advantage to learn how. Venture to the Iron Front, slay a Wargronn, and retrieve its harness. You may want to find help."}
d[39648]={de="The children have gone missing! That horrible Grumpus has been making his way throughout Draenor, snatching up children. Please save them! Our scouts have spotted him over in Frostfire Ridge."}
d[39649]={de="The grumplings are horrid creatures. They're the ones doin' the dirty work for Grumpus. If you're able to remove the threat I'm sure rescuing the children won't be much of a problem."}
d[39651]={de="One of Draenor's oldest stories is the legend of Grumpus. The story tells of a mean-spirited brute that would come in the night, in the dead of winter, and kidnap children that misbehaved. Back at his lair, he would present them with awful toys, and use their tears to spawn his minions. But Grumpus is no legend, he's real and he's taken our children! Please, you have to slay him!"}
d[39668]={de="That mean old Grumpus has amassed a collection of odd gifts. He's deliberately trying to crush the spirit of children everywhere by giving out the worst presents imaginable. Take this spirit bomb. Toss it on some of Grumpus's unusual gifts and take them out for good! We're in this together, {name}. Now go and save the spirit of the holiday!"}
d[39716]={de="The Bonefleet once raided trading ships traveling the waters of Draenor. One such ship carried farming supplies intended for Elodor. Now, they use these supplies to sow their plague into our earth. From the putrid mounds sprout vegetative horrors. These abominations must be destroyed, before they can spread across the landscape."}
d[39719]={de="Each year, around this time, there is a strange surge of spiritual energy across Draenor. Beckoned by this phenomenon, a ghastly fleet of undead pirates emerges from the mist. We call it the Bonefleet. The Bonefleet is led by a savage pirate known as Bonerender. He seeks nothing more than the complete destruction of all of the living of Draenor. Seek out Bonerender and defeat him, before he sails back into the mist once again."}
d[39720]={de="The Bonefleet wants nothing more than to spread their undead curse onto dry land. Like a sickness, it will slowly overtake the landscape if left unchecked. The stench of undeath permeates the barrels of fertilizer they use to sow their dread crops. They are the source of the spreading plague, and must be destroyed."}
d[39721]={de="If we're going to protect Draenor from the Bonefleet menace, we'll need to thin out the crew. See to a swift reduction in their numbers, and we might just push them back into the sea for another year."}
d[47895]={de="If I'm going to clean up Gnomeregan, I've got to be ready to battle all manner of rat, roach, and potentially even the dreaded mutant rat-roach. What I'm saying is that I need to put these bots to the test! A real, live-action field demo. Are your pets up for a code review?"}
d[50791]={de="<Kua'fon rests with his head under his wing.> Skree... <Perhaps the little guy could use a display of affection to raise his spirits.>"}
d[50796]={de="<Kua'fon opens his maw and issues a continuous screech.> SKREEEEEEEEEEEEE!!! <You know what to do.>"}
d[50798]={de="Ah, there you are. Kua'fon ran off into de jungle. I saw him head down de western path out of the Kraal but beyond that I could not say where he may have gone. This kind of thing happens with the young. Our winged companions have a keen sense of adventure! It would be helpful if yours could fly, but it is not yet time. I would check any reasonably high place that he could climb to, as a start."}
d[50801]={de="Ah, yes, I was wondering when you would come to check on your little one. As you have likely noticed, he is not here. Little ones are very curious and often seek to leave the nest before they are ready. It is often the brooding mother's job to keep them from wandering. What, did you think I was going to stop him? <Wingminder Goja laughs.> I heard some screeching to de west. Best hurry, or you may not have a hatchling to look after!"}
d[50842]={de="Kua'fon was peering over de edge and managed to fall off de cliff again. Normally he gets back up here on his own, but it be taking too long this time. Best go down to de beach and find him. He is probably stuck up one of de ship masts out there. If he will not come down, you can try bribing him with more fish."}
d[50930]={de="<Kua'fon looks to the kite, then back at you. He looks to the kite again, poking his head forward deliberately. He slowly pans his gaze back to you.> Skree. <Time for another flight!>"}
d[51146]={de="You know, I think Kua'fon might be lonely when you are not here. What makes me say that? Well, I got a very angry scroll from a Tortollan indicating he was stealing shiny things from their stalls, but that could mean anything. You should probably stop him before he damages your reputation, hm? <Wingminder Goja cackles.>"}
d[52317]={de="<Kua'fon places a troll skull into your palm. It is covered in teeth marks and rather slimy.> Skree! <Kua'fon peers at you expectantly.>"}
d[54082]={de="Welcome back, dear test subject. My dear sister has kindly asked me to administer today's experiment, which falls below our typical standards of legality... You may, as always, choose not to participate and we will acquire sufficient replacement test subjects. Our new project requires more energy than our generator can manage. We must supercharge it with a jolt of power from the outside. Bondo's Yard has the best power line in Mechagon, so we shall siphon what we need from those rapscallions."}
d[54090]={de="Ricket sent word that she was here in Mechagon, so I came right away to help with the uh... research. I had the peons scour the island for any technology they could find. With da stuff we got here, we gonna make some amazing weapons to fight King Mechagon. Then afterwards, we get rich selling 'em! Help me wrangle everyone's ideas into one perfect weapon!"}
d[55213]={de="The wondrous scuttlebutt around town is that the charging station in Bondo's Yard is going to be repaired today! That charging station is the best way to recharge all the Empty Energy Cells that've been piling up in your bag. Or in other people's bag. Or inside the mechanical innards of robots you don't own but are legally allowed to destroy. After you've acquired Empty Energy Cells, help build the charging station in Bondo's Yard and charge all of your Empty Energy Cells!"}
d[55244]={de="<The Child of Torcali stares longingly out of her pen. Her gaze seems to be following the other nearby direhorns. Perhaps she could use a distraction.>"}
d[55245]={de="<The Child of Torcali investigates your hands for traces of food and makes a small sound of distress.>"}
d[55246]={de="Ever since Torcali gave her boon to de little one, she has been growing like a weed. Dat makes her very hungry. She got out again to look for more things to eat. Before you ask, it is not my role to stop her from doing what she wants. Only to ensure she is safe. She is probably fine. Bring her home, and if you have trouble bringing her home, you might try a bribe."}
d[55248]={de="You have done an adequate job keeping de little one fed, but sometimes they just want something else. I did not see where de hatchling went, but you should start where de grass is real green. You will likely find her eating it. If you have trouble bringing her home, you might try a bribe."}
d[55250]={de="<The Child of Torcali investigates your hands for traces of food and makes a small sound of distress.>"}
d[55251]={de="It has long been remarked upon that a direhorn is de bravest beast in de jungle. That is why they are chosen as mounts for our warriors. In this case, that bravery may not be in your favor. De little one has run off and I do not think she is hungry this time. Best find her before she gets hurt."}
d[55299]={de="<Danielle Anglers may be interested in this fish.>"}
d[55305]={de="<Danielle Anglers may be interested in this fish.>"}
d[55306]={de="<Danielle Anglers may be interested in this fish.>"}
d[55307]={de="<Danielle Anglers may be interested in this fish.>"}
d[55308]={de="<Danielle Anglers may be interested in this fish.>"}
d[55309]={de="<Danielle Anglers may be interested in this fish.>"}
d[55310]={de="<Danielle Anglers may be interested in this fish.>"}
d[55311]={de="<Danielle Anglers may be interested in this fish.>"}
d[55312]={de="<Danielle Anglers may be interested in this fish.>"}
d[55313]={de="<Danielle Anglers may be interested in this fish.>"}
d[55378]={de="I've received an urgent request from Tinkmaster Overspark. These supplies are needed!"}
d[55379]={de="I've received an urgent request from Tinkmaster Overspark. These supplies are needed!"}
d[55380]={de="I've received an urgent request from Tinkmaster Overspark. These supplies are needed!"}
d[55381]={de="Gazlowe's orders are in: He wants these supplies ASAP. Ya got the goods?"}
d[55382]={de="Gazlowe's orders are in: He wants these supplies ASAP. Ya got the goods?"}
d[55383]={de="Gazlowe's orders are in: He wants these supplies ASAP. Ya got the goods?"}
d[55463]={de="Look at what they've done to this island, {name}. Nature is nearly extinguished, its death cry falling on the deaf ears of mechagnomes. But I have heard the teeny tiny animals of Mechagon, and bring aid from afar! It won't be easy to restore balance to a land so severely wounded. Nature's scars run deep here. Thankfully, we are not alone. I've brought living sap from Nordrassil, the World Tree of Mount Hyjal. Use it to regrow the forests and speed nature's recovery in this land."}
d[55528]={de="The troggs have been raiding our supplies since we got here, but now that we got some fire power you're going to put a stop to that! Let's teach them troggs to stay away from our stuff!"}
d[55575]={de="The garbage in these trash heaps is full of rare metals: Dalaranium, Suramarite, even Gnomeisium! I've not seen this much easy gold to be had, since they left the vault door open in Boralus! You help me collect some of the metal, and my friend Gao will sell it on the black market. I've got a device that can tear the metal right out of the trash!"}
d[55658]={de="Before King Mechagon claimed this island, someone else lived here. Buried beneath this filth and garbage is the history of a forgotten people. With your help, we shall learn about these previous inhabitants. Sir Finley has marked a location where he's seen unusual artifacts. Meet him there and see if you can discover any clues."}
d[55672]={de="The text on this parchment appears to be Tortollan. Is it possible that Tortollans once resided on this island? We need to act quickly, before the creatures in this area destroy anymore evidence. Search the area for any signs of Tortollan relics."}
d[55688]={de="This runestone could be of Vrykul origins. Is it possible that Vrykul once visited this island? Where there's one runestone, there's usually more. The roots of lashers are drawn to the magic of runestones. If there are more buried here, the Lasher roots maybe wrapped around them! Clear these lashers and see if any have runestones tangled in their roots."}
d[55695]={de="Once every week, Mechagon expels a lot of excess oils through the outflow. That's why the place is a toxic mess! Today they expelled a batch of Golden Cogpaste. The stuff is amazing! I make air fresheners out of it. Makes any mount smell like it's brand new! Check all the pipes in the outflow, and see if you can collect some of this paste."}
d[55717]={de="That card you found was a gold rare Huolon! I think that card belonged to Adalin Halfheight, one of our junior explorer league members. If he dropped it, he and our other junior members maybe in trouble! We need to find Leona Mistcaller, Dunkin Crackjaw, and Adalin Halfheight immediately!"}
d[55718]={de="<A very old ring of Nightelf origin. Seems out of place on this island, perhaps Elise Starseeker will know what to make of it>"}
d[55743]={de="<Recycling is fun and profitable. The Recyclerizer DX-82 stands ready to receive more scrap metal.>"}
d[55765]={de="You got a problem with mechanical bugs, so the Roughriders are here to sort this mess out! In my experience, this big of an outbreak must have some sort of queen bug behind it all. We gonna go in, kill a lot of bugs till we find the leader of 'em all. Horde or Alliance don't matter, you're with the Roughriders today. Let's kill some bugs!"}
d[55813]={de="This conspiracy of ravens is preying on citizens of Rustbolt, it's unacceptable! Prince Erazmin has asked me to reduce their numbers, but I could really use your help. Can you help me kill some of them? Use my marker gun if you need it. I'll blast the ones you mark, and help bring them down."}
d[55815]={de="Madam Goya is interested in many unusual items other than just rare metals. Keep an eye out for these particular items during your travels in Nazjatar. Deliver them to me and Madam Goya will consider you for special access."}
d[55816]={de="In my travels of the many possible futures, I discovered another place much like Rustbolt, but different. In this other time and place, very little is alive, everything is machines. You must travel to this other place. You will scan the memory banks of the Clockwork Giants you find there. Then we will use that data to ensure that our Rustbolt never becomes the other place."}
d[55880]={de="Welcome back, dear test subject. Today's experiment is... <Pristy flips through some papers and smiles.> ...My pet project, the NRG-100! I am quite pleased with the potential improvements I've made to efficiency, potency, and destructivity. And the only thing I had to sacrifice was stability! When you're ready to proceed, strap on the NRG-100."}
d[55885]={de="Some of our Roughriders are missing, I tried to find them, but got pinned down here by the bugs! I could really use your help, {name}. See if you can save my missing troopers."}
d[55905]={de="We got actual ABDUCTIONS happenin' here, {name}! Honest to gold, flying robots are swoopin' into town and snatchin' up people like it's closin' time at Gallywix's buffet! Lucky for the Rustbolt Resistance, Gazlowe called in me and my explosives to save the day. You wanna pitch in? Take one of my rocket launchers and blast those containment crates outta the sky. Whatever they've got trapped inside will come tumblin' down real fast, so you gotta run underneath and catch 'em."}
d[55994]={de="These troggs watch everything we do. They see us pouring oil into various machines, so now they're stealing the oil and drinking it. I think they believe it's going to turn them into machines! We need that oil back, before they drink it all!"}
d[56049]={de="That ooze seems really hungry! He ate my backpack, compass, pickaxe, and my hearthstone cards. Get my cards back!"}
d[56053]={de="Those of us with enough mechanization survived, but it didn't matter. Bondo Bigblock sold us out. In exchange for full mechanization, he built giant bots and attacked Rustbolt. He will continue to act against us, till those few of us left are dead. We must remove this threat immediately."}
d[56082]={de="Those bots have been attacking us from the moment we landed. We've got to hold this beach! My expedition guards could use your help, {name}. Lend a hand, destroy bots on the beach and in the nearby woodlands."}
d[56083]={de="Those rampaging bots ain't lettin' up! We're payin' good money for the best and brightest goblins on the planet, and I ain't gonna let some malfunctionin' machinery take 'em outta the shift schedule. This is textbook unsafe working conditions, and the Greasemonkey Union reps are givin' me an earful for it. Protect the workers!"}
d[56116]={de="<WARNING 3.6.4 - Y: Keep all appendages clear of doors or risk irreversible limb recyclerization.>"}
d[56142]={de="Izira Gearsworn is still alive, she is Rustbolt's strongest fighter, but her legs are broken. If we're going to survive I need parts to repair and upgrade her. There are machines all over with parts we can salvage. With some perseverance we should be able to fix Izira's legs. Help me obtain the following parts."}
d[56184]={de="I finally found it! This is the resting place of my father, after his crew mutinied and left him here to die. I've scouted the island, and found the locations of three chests that contain mementoes of my father. Do this for me and my family. Recover my father's sword, clothing, and bones from the three chests I've marked."}
d[56301]={de="I've heard lot's of stories about dead fathers, mothers, and family treasures. Don't believe any of it. We're all here to get any pirate gold, before these mecha-fools get it first! If there's gold to be had here, it's in that fat chest the murlocs are guarding. Kill their chief, empty out the chest, and we'll split it fifty-fifty, since I'm telling ya about it."}
d[56306]={de="Darn pirates stole my jewels... err, I mean my sister's... uh, mom's jewelry. Yeah, that's the story! Point is, they stole it, and it's all out there strewn around in the mud, and treasure chests. Maybe on a few of the robots and murlocs. My mom's not greedy, she just wants a few of the necklaces with gold and lots of diamonds. I'd pay ya for those."}
d[56324]={de="You lookin' to charge some energy cells off of our tower of power? I ain't surprised - everyone is. And everyone PAYS. You got that or I got ta say it again? <Flux spits behind her.> I can tell you're a first-timer. Bondo's got a special deal for you flashfoots. Small access fee, one charge only. Deal? You ain't gettin' any other offers."}
d[56326]={de="A conspiracy of ravens is preying on citizens of Rustbolt! It's most unacceptable! Prince Erazmin has asked me to rescue as many citizens as I can, but I could use your help. I've tracked the ravens to this hill. We blast the ravens out of the sky, and you rescue the mechagnomes. Use my marker gun if you need help bringing the ravens down."}
d[56327]={de="Chopping up bots is my business. Any bots you bring to my scrapper will be broken up into useful parts. It's a win for both of us! Use the Bot-Energizer to bring me dead bots, and we'll break them into spare parts."}
d[56334]={de="It's loose up there! I told them not to do it, but they didn't listen. Now it's gone out of control and killed everyone up there. It's an experimental Whirlbot. They never should have built it! You need to stop it before it comes down here looking for more victims! Kill the Whirling Zap-O-Matic."}
d[56335]={de="You lookin' to charge some energy cells off of our tower of power? I ain't surprised - everyone is. And everyone PAYS. You got that or I got ta say it again? <Flux spits behind her.> I can tell you're a first-timer. Bondo's got a special deal for you flashfoots. Small access fee, one charge only. Deal? You ain't gettin' any other offers."}
d[56341]={de="<Direbrew's Dark Iron have fled, leaving behind a small piece of one of their mole machines. Perhaps your Dark Iron allies would be interested in hearing of your victory.>"}
d[56355]={de="A weapon like this could really turn the tide against King Mechagons Troops. Let's go see how their gear matches up against our new toy. Take out King Mechagon's Sentries wherever you can find them"}
d[56361]={de="I've received an urgent request from Tinkmaster Overspark. These supplies are needed!"}
d[56362]={de="Gazlowe's orders are in: He wants these supplies ASAP. Ya got the goods?"}
d[56363]={de="I've received an urgent request from Tinkmaster Overspark. These supplies are needed!"}
d[56364]={de="Gazlowe's orders are in: He wants these supplies ASAP. Ya got the goods?"}
d[56365]={de="You exist here due to a time anomaly, but you must return to your own time and help us there. The Visual Holo Sphere from the Vaultbot nearby contains the data necessary to defeat King Mechagon before he can use the Mechoriginator. Deliver the Visual Holo Sphere to me in your reality. With luck I will be able to rewind history and prevent this existence from ever happening."}
d[56372]={de="<The hozen have been successfully chased away, and Brewfest saved once again. The question asks itself, though: How did hozen get to Dun Morogh? Perhaps you should ask somebody who has experience in navigation and travel.>"}
d[56373]={de="The Bubble-eyed Rolly used to be plentiful in the nearby pond. Last week they all started to vanish! A large water elemental has been swallowing all the fish! They are still alive, just swimming around inside the elemental now. I need you to kill that elemental, and catch three Bubbly-eyed Rolly so I can examine their condition."}
d[56380]={de="One of King Mechagon's older Aerial units is having mechanical problems and is grounded nearby. They're trying to get it repaired, so we need to act fast while it's vulnerable. Destroy the Aerial Patroller XZ-2 before they can get it repaired."}
d[56402]={de="It may be too late for some of our fallen brothers and sisters, but it is not too late to give solace to their families. Every Wastewander carries with them a unique coin, signifying their status as a member of our group. If you find any of these coins, please bring them to me and I will make sure they are properly returned to their next of kin."}
d[56405]={de="You Rustbolt resisters inspire me. Tinkering, building, exploring. Letting your imagination run wild and then chasing after it, wherever it leads, with reckless abandon! <Walton releases a deep sigh.> I miss those days. I hope, someday, my conscience will allow me to stay on the surface with you all permanently... Before I return to Mechagon, we must build something incredible. Waren and I have identified a large number of extra construction project sites for today. Build with boldness!"}
d[56410]={de="King Mechagon unit in possession of Norgannon disk. Data is corrupted, possession of such data is dangerous. Please aid in the recovery of Corrupted Disk Fragments that have been discarded via Mechagon waste systems. Deliver recovered Corrupted Disc Fragment to Data Analyzer R33-DR for purging."}
d[56434]={de="Responsible for a spree of mayhem and chaos throughout the Heaps, resulting in the theft of energy cells, spare parts, and the consumption of Improbable Mechano-Chicken Wings without payment. Special caution around Roadtrogg, who has demonstrated a violent attitude towards living things. Elimination of these two felons is of the highest priority."}
d[56469]={de="<An old pirate hat. Seems out of place on this island, perhaps Reno Jackson will know what to make of it>"}
d[56471]={de="This land is already a monumental disaster, but it could get worse! The Venture Company is here, and will exploit this land for every ounce of profit they can make. We must make their venture here unprofitable, so they will leave. Destroy the three expensive security units with them, and they may leave for more profitable ventures."}
d[56493]={de="Maokka has such a gentle heart. He is so good with the little ones, always playing games and telling stories. We do however really dislike these Venture Co. individuals, so I suggest a more direct approach. Try killing them all."}
d[56501]={de="<This box of rockets could just be used to take out the Venture Co. Balloons. That would really motivate Venture Co. to go somewhere else.>"}
d[56508]={de="<There's a variety of parts around this area that might be useful to Rustbolt. You should collect them before Venture Co takes them.>"}
d[56523]={de="If you've spent any time with that arrogant nitwit, Overspark, you know why I'm here. To silence his boasting and finally prove that my inventions are better! I've released countless mechanical chickens across this island to analyze the technology here, adopt it, and evolve their own circuitry. One of them will become my ultimate battle chicken! But those idiot troggs think my chickens are edible and keep bashing them. Protect them, so my techno-evolutionary experiment can run its course."}
d[56532]={de="These motospiders continue to multiply unchecked. If we don't slow them down they'll overrun Rustbolt soon. I've modified Norbit here with adequate firepower to take the spiders head on! Would you pilot Norbit and destroy the Reinforced Sparkweave Eggs?"}
d[56550]={de="Our friends continue to fall as these terrible insects pour of their nests and attack our camps. It's a terrible job to ask of anyone, but we have to dispose of the corpses as quickly as possible. We can't allow our dead to be used as fertilizer for growing their disgusting eggs."}
d[56552]={de="Gazlowe hired you for protection too? I guess it's true that he only hires the best, eh? Ha! Pay's great, but the rules are dung: no fightin' in town, no exceptions. Bah! <Usha takes a big gulp of her drink.> That tiny tender prince won't give us his tech unless he thinks we're good little angels... Ha! But Gazlowe didn't say nothin' about fightin' outside of town. I got my own squad on the outskirts, ready to brawl with Grumbol's guzzlers if they show their bearded faces. You want in?"}
d[56557]={de="There are only two things more fun than fighting, and the first is talking trash! <Usha shouts an insult at Grumbol Grimhammer.> That boar-beard runt over there's been a thorn in my backside since Alterac... Can't seem to shake him. We got a bet going about who's the best fighter on the island. You want to help me win this wager?"}
d[56558]={de="*buuuurrp* Arrrright, listen 'ere. We got ourselves a bit o' a predicament. Besides this dump's ale tastin' like oil, that pigheaded Usha here been sayin' some unfortunate stuff about our troops. Unfortunate FOR HER, 'cuz now *uuuuurp* gonna needya ta rough up any Horde swine ya end up runnin' into out there. Loosely speakin' we ain't supposed to be brawlin' out 'ere, so this ain't a formal order or nothin'..."}
d[56559]={de="'Ey, {name}, I could be usin' yer talents fer a little bet I got goin' on with Usha. I'm wagerin' you can beat up five 'o her pals around the island before her dog can beat up five o' ours. Ye up fer it me lad? 'O course ya are, ahahaha!"}
d[56572]={de="I must share the wonders of this place with all of Azeroth in a way that will entertain young and old alike. I will use the technology here to create a new line of toys unlike anything seen before! My Quasi-Faceted scanner can help construct perfect replicas of things here on the island. I just need a helpful individual such as yourself to scan a few things around this area."}
d[56573]={de="First, let me say that you will ALWAYS be our favorite test subject. But our experiments require far more sacrifice than a single test subject can offer. And, from time to time, some of those test subjects require new limbs. My dear brother and I have a nascent concept for expanding the average lifespan of mechanical appendages. But we've run out of components to experiment on. Salvage some appendages from the heap outside town so we can continue our experiments."}
d[56621]={de="When I say that power is life, I'm not speaking figuratively, my dear test subject. Properly harnessed, power can create life itself--or at least a close enough facsimile for our purposes. There is a massive reserve of discarded technology lurking deep in the mucky depths of the Outflow. As usual, Mechagon's trash is our treasure. I've finally perfected my device that will animate the sludge to bring that technology up to the surface for you. All you have to do is pop 'em and grab the tech!"}
d[56715]={de="<The hozen have been successfully chased away, and Brewfest saved once again. The question asks itself, though: How did hozen get to Durotar? Perhaps somebody in the Brewfest grounds has experience with them.>"}
d[56716]={de="<Direbrew's Dark Iron have fled, leaving behind a small piece of one of their mole machines. You know they have attacked Brewfest before. Perhaps one of the goblins would be interested in hearing of your victory.>"}
d[56746]={de="I'm sure you agree that Pascal-K1N6 is the greatest invention you've ever seen! If you're not convinced yet, try to push him to his limits. I don't mind! Bring him more resources and blueprints -- he'll craft anything you need!"}
d[56747]={de="I've received an urgent request from Tinkmaster Overspark. These supplies are needed!"}
d[56749]={de="Gazlowe's orders are in: He wants these supplies ASAP. Ya got the goods?"}
d[56750]={de="Gazlowe's orders are in: He wants these supplies ASAP. Ya got the goods?"}
d[56751]={de="I've received an urgent request from Tinkmaster Overspark. These supplies are needed!"}
d[56752]={de="Gazlowe's orders are in: He wants these supplies ASAP. Ya got the goods?"}
d[56753]={de="I've received an urgent request from Tinkmaster Overspark. These supplies are needed!"}
d[56754]={de="Gazlowe's orders are in: He wants these supplies ASAP. Ya got the goods?"}
d[56755]={de="I've received an urgent request from Tinkmaster Overspark. These supplies are needed!"}
d[56757]={de="I've received an urgent request from Tinkmaster Overspark. These supplies are needed!"}
d[56758]={de="Gazlowe's orders are in: He wants these supplies ASAP. Ya got the goods?"}
d[56759]={de="Gazlowe's orders are in: He wants these supplies ASAP. Ya got the goods?"}
d[56760]={de="I've received an urgent request from Tinkmaster Overspark. These supplies are needed!"}
d[56761]={de="I've received an urgent request from Tinkmaster Overspark. These supplies are needed!"}
d[56762]={de="Gazlowe's orders are in: He wants these supplies ASAP. Ya got the goods?"}
d[56763]={de="I've received an urgent request from Tinkmaster Overspark. These supplies are needed!"}
d[56765]={de="Gazlowe's orders are in: He wants these supplies ASAP. Ya got the goods?"}
d[56889]={de="Ahh, my friend, have you returned to render additional aid? As you can see, we are still locked in battle with these creatures, with no end to their numbers in sight. This is a war of attrition and we find ourselves at a clear disadvantage as injuries continue to mount. Please, assist any of our wounded that you find within the ruins."}
d[57278]={de="I swore to the grave of Vistara the Fallen that I would bring him the head of the one who betrayed him. Though that was eons ago, it is an oath I must fulfill. Whatever fate ultimately befell the traitor, it is likely that his head can still be found nearby. Slaughter everyone here. Surely one of them must be the traitor... or be in possession of his head."}
d[57284]={de="The finest sword in existence has been lost! Never in your pitiful adventures have you encountered such a blade, mortal. Foe Cleaver was forged to strike down the titans themselves! I have wielded it against countless adversaries. Emissaries of the Light, minions of the Void, meddlers from the Gardens of Life... all have fallen before me! Soon the very planes of reality will kneel to my greatness! Once I find my weapon, that is. I insist you help me reclaim it. I know it's here somewhere!"}
d[57326]={de="<Gazlowe pulls you in close and whispers.> Lookit here, {name}. I gotta keep my nose clean here in front of the prince. But I trust you know what's gotta be done outside of town, yeah? Outside of town... where all the tech is... Tech that Alliance grubs are tryin' to get their clumsy mitts on... which we could use for the Horde... to build big weapons... and scary robots... and other lucrative products...? I don't gotta spell this out for you, right?"}
d[57327]={de="<Overspark pulls you in close and whispers.> As the leader of this momentous expedition, I must stay with Prince Erazmin to ensure he's not swindled by this Horde hooligan. But I cannot stop my research, or the Horde will gain the advantage! Underlings like yourself must collect the technology samples required to fuel my legendary brainstorms. Bring me prototypes from the island, and I will turn them into groundbreaking new innovations for the Alliance!"}
d[57718]={de="Some of our warriors were camped in the small settlement near Guo-Lai when the Baruk invaded the area. Some managed to escape, but they returned with tales of their brothers and sisters in arms being petrified by the mogu stoneshapers into living statues! We can't leave our warriors behind! The stoneshapers must carry some means to reverse the spell and free them from their stone prisons. Bring our soldiers back!"}
d[57721]={de="The warring clans are relentless and our warriors are going through armor faster than I can keep it repaired. If you find yourself in battle with the other clans, see if you can salvage any undamaged armor pieces from their soldiers. We should not let good resources go to waste."}
d[57737]={de="Mar'at was overrun by those foul K'thir before we could safely evacuate our citizens. I fear the worst has happened to them. Please, if anyone is left alive within the city, tell them to come to Ramkahen."}
d[57773]={de="Our warriors have observed foul manifestations coming forth from numerous void tears within the surrounding jungle. They have been but mere weaklings, clearly intended to test our defenses before the real forces arrive. If we do not deal with this threat now, however, it will only be a matter of time until we are overrun by their fodder. Find a way to close those portals!"}
d[57774]={de="Scouts have returned recently, nearly on the verge of death, with reports that I find... disconcerting. Neferset have been spotted wandering the streets of their city to the south. This would normally be no cause for alarm, except the Neferset were completely wiped out. I must ask you to investigate further... and if by some foul magic these reports turn out to be true, you must do whatever you can to contain this threat!"}
d[57964]={de="There's still a lot of us here, trying to survive in these ruins. These constructs have been encroaching on us constantly. They steal what they can, and haul off any of us they capture to be recycled in their labs. The solution here requires an extensive use of violence, by you!"}
d[57968]={de="Is there no end to these foul monsters!? I cannot abide the desecration of our dead, especially not as fodder for this disgusting insect army. Destroy as many as you can, preferably with fire!"}
d[58151]={de="The howling winds that surround us may some day be drowned out, masked by these increasingly dark, yet familiar whispers. Something must be done. Enter the darkness, {name}, and strike down the enemy."}
d[58155]={de="Imagine being trapped in a world you didn't know existed--a reality unbeknownst to even yourself. Thoughts, fears, and dark desires cloud the mind, coupled with irresistible temptation. So many are lost to the darkness, unable to resist these temptations, but not all. Do what you can to preserve those that fight against the darkness. We mustn't allow them to fall."}
d[58156]={de="The darkness grows. The cycle continues. Do what you can to stay N'Zoth's efforts. If we do not stand against the corruption we may some day find ourselves drowning in darkness."}
d[58167]={de="Waves of darkness continue their assault on the shores of our world. I am afraid the waters at our feet may soon wash over us. Perhaps it is time for a different approach. Make your way into the twisted realm and seek out their dark portals. If we are able to slow their advance it might just buy us the time needed to expose a fatal weakness."}
d[58168]={de="Their eyes are upon us, {name}, watching every move from the shadows. It is no wonder our efforts thus far have felt... lacking. The fault is by no means your own. We should have suspected this was the case long ago. If we are to continue our efforts with meaningful expectations we must go undetected. Our old friend has offered an elixir to aide in exposing our enemy. While there may be a few... unknown side effects, the result provides the imbiber true sight in the darkness."}
d[58211]={de="When this necropolis collapsed, plenty of its parts got submerged in the riverbed flowing just outside. I hope you're really dedicated to fixing this place, because we're gonna dredge those parts back up! Take this pump. If you find any places bubbling in that sludge, that's a good sign parts will be there! Just be careful with whatever you pull up! You could face some resistance."}
d[58230]={de="Strange forces have been interfering with my visions of late. The ever-watching eyes pierce through the veil, shattering my clairvoyance. The eyes of our enemy peer into our very souls and pierce our minds. We must rip them out, if we truly wish to be rid of the curse on this land."}
d[58231]={de="In my visions I hear... voices... Their words are nonsense, but over time patterns arise. I believe there is something important behind what these voices say, but I have yet to decipher a word. We will need to learn from the source. Find any writings you can among the cultists who travel with these dark creatures. Their ramblings may be the key to understanding the message beneath this madness."}
d[58232]={de="It has been a long time since the tol'vir have squared off against the forces of an Old God, so our tactical knowledge of their forces is limited. However, one tenet of combat always holds true -- striking down those that issue the orders will weaken the foe much greater than the rank and file. I have observed that the larger faceless minions act as commanders of the Old Gods' forces. Silence them, and perhaps we can sow a different kind of chaos in their ranks."}
d[58233]={de="While the fleshbeasts that accompany the invading forces appear to be no more than a nuisance, they carry within themselves a deep connection to the corrupting powers of the Old Gods. Like a pestilence, they spread the N'Zoth's corruption wherever they tread, slowly twisting the very land to their form. They must be eradicated."}
d[58234]={de="My clairvoyance provides a great strategic asset to the people of Ramkahen. However, the potency of my visions of late has proven taxing to my health. I have devised a tonic that may serve to dull the harm these visions cause, but it will require the coalesced essence of the Old Gods' corruption. If you could retrieve some samples of this for me, it could prove invaluable in our efforts."}
d[58235]={de="This invasion struck us without warning, with structures reminiscent of the Black Empire materializing out of nothing, pouring out the forces of the Old Gods. We have no idea how they came to be or where they came from. However, whenever a new structure appears, it is preceded by malefic obelisks. We believe these obelisks act as anchors to usher in more of the Old Gods' forces. If we truly wish to stem the tide of this invasion, we must destroy the obelisks."}
d[58237]={de="Every moment that N'Zoth's forces remain in Uldum, his corruption seeps further into the land itself. Even if we were to drive back his minions, the damage he has done to Uldum may be irreversible. We must seek out his corruption where it festers and eliminate it."}
d[58238]={de="Our citizens here in Ramkahen have managed to escape the brunt of N'Zoth's assault. Our brothers in the Lost City were not so fortunate. Those not immediately slain have been held captive only to be tortured by N'Zoth's minions. I know that you will be taking the fight to N'Zoth's forces. If you can free our allies as well, Ramkahen will be in your debt."}
d[58239]={de="The Wastewanders have spent many generations as brigands, whether on land or sea. Though we have decided to hang up that life for a chance at a more peaceful existence, we have not forgotten the lessons we've learned in those days. One such lesson I feel is particularly relevant now -- when faced with a superior opponent, it often helps to use their weapons against them. Find their hidden caches and take whatever you can carry. You may just find something that can turn the tide of this battle."}
d[58260]={de="A swarm of marrowbore queens have been laying eggs atop the ruins of our house. We may be able to use this to our advantage. With Twigin's help, eliminate the queens and recover larvae from the eggs. I have a plan for the larvae that may allow us to use the marrowbore to our advantage."}
d[58277]={de="The Old Gods have many faceless minions at their disposal, but none so deceiving as the ones they call k'thir. Though not nearly as imposing as their brethren, the k'thir manipulate in the shadows, bending the wills of men and even reality itself. We must not allow their machinations to go unchecked."}
d[58281]={de="Fighting a war on several fronts has taken its toll on our supplies. Our blacksmiths cannot repair and replace our soldiers' armor quickly enough, which is leaving us ill-equipped to face so many foes. Though the Amathet's armor is ancient, it is titan-forged and formidable. If we were able to salvage any, it could prove very useful to our defensive efforts. Can you help?"}
d[58282]={de="The archers of Ramkahen are highly skilled, but the bows of the Amathet have the advantage of range. This makes our incursions into their territory highly dangerous. You have a knack for fighting behind enemy lines. If you could thin out their ranks, it could provide us an opportunity to push their lines back for once. Will you help?"}
d[58283]={de="The Sun Priests are an ancient order for the tol'vir who have walked among all of the tribes. Those that follow the Amathet, however, have twisted our beliefs and weaponized them to justify their crusade against Ramkahen. Their soldiers follow them blindly, never questioning. They must be stopped."}
d[58284]={de="Very little is known about the Sun King that leads the Amathet. Our observations suggest that those closest to him are the \"Suntouched,\" a unique caste of solar magic practitioners. I would like very much to learn more about this Sun King but, unlike some members of the Explorers' League, I'm not willing to risk the lives of my researchers to do so. You seem to be able to hold your own, though. If you happen upon any records about the Sun King, I'd gladly take them off your hands."}
d[58285]={de="Ever since the Amathet came out of their tombs, they've been busy unearthing titan relics from the surrounding areas. I'm not sure what they intend to do with them or if they're just hoarding it so we can't have them. Sufficed to say the Explorers' League would love to study some of what they found! Of course, we can't get anywhere close to them without the Amathet trying to stick an axe in us, but that's not a problem for you, is it? Care to help?"}
d[58286]={de="The Amathet's conquest of eastern Uldum was sudden, and we were unable to reach some of our farthest settlements in time. Fortunately, many of the tol'vir who lived in the conquered territories were not killed, instead being put to work under the Amathet's whip. We must take any opportunity we can to free them and return them to their homes."}
d[58287]={de="Reports from my scouts mention various idols and monuments that the Amathet use to channel their solar magic. I don't know exactly what they're up to, but we should take away any possible advantage they have. So, I want you to go over there, and break anything that looks remotely magical. Just don't tell the Explorers' League. I'll never hear the end of it."}
d[58288]={de="On the surface the Amathet appear to be unwavering, but all soldiers have their breaking point. We need to send a message to their forces that we are not to be trifled with. Seek out the strongest of their numbers and bring them down in front of their eyes. We will show them the strength of Uldum!"}
d[58289]={de="From what we know about the Amathet, they must've been locked away in their tombs for thousands of years. Just think of what we could learn from them! Of course, that would be a lot easier if they weren't trying to kill us. If you happen upon any caches of Amathet relics in your travels, let me know. I'd love to see what sort of mysteries they contain!"}
d[58291]={de="The Wastewanders used the pelts of the local hyenas to construct our armor. Unfortunately since the Amathet arrived, their hunters have overrun our normal hunting grounds. We need those pelts, and will pay handsomely for them. Either take them from the hunters or skin the hyenas yourself, if you have the skill."}
d[58321]={de="Our scouts have reported that the Amathet are constructing new titanic watchers. We had long thought this art was lost to the sands of time. It would appear we were mistaken. I needn't tell you what a boon it would be to have the aid of watcher constructs in our battles for Uldum. We must unlock the secrets of their construction! The power of a titanic watcher lies in its core. I ask that you bring one to me, so that our artificers might divine its construction."}
d[58454]={de="Your contribution of anima has aided our operation here greatly. Several of our more famous competitors have come here lured by the flow of new anima. Would you like to test yourself versus the famous Sabriel? There could be much profit for everyone, if you were to defeat her. I can add her to the schedule, she will appear soon if you defeat the other challengers."}
d[58462]={de="Were it not enough for our enemy to apply deadly force against us, their minions also strike into the very heart of our defenders. I speak, of course, of the eyes. They peer into the souls of our warriors and produce their darkest fears against them. If we have any hope to defeat this foe, they must be destroyed."}
d[58469]={de="As N'Zoth's influence spreads within the Vale, our very reality begins to break down. The Old God's power has created tears in the fabric our world, acting as doorways for his minions to invade from his dark realm. As long as these tears exist, we will never be free from N'Zoth's grasp. Close them, and stem the tide of his corruption!"}
d[58470]={de="I understand that the Black Empire poses a grave threat to Pandaria, but we may also use this as an opportunity! Though we've faced them several times before, very little is known about the Old Gods or N'Zoth's mysterious realm of Ny'alotha. When studying ancient civilizations, we often rely on artifacts to unlock the deepest mysteries lost to time. I wonder if some such artifacts could be found among the Old God's forces? It can't hurt to check, right?"}
d[58471]={de="Even given the Sha's origins with the Old Gods, we in Pandaria still know very little of them. I would like to take this opportunity to add whatever information I can about them to the archives of the Lorewalkers. Of course, that becomes a bit problematic when they're trying to kill us. That doesn't seem to be a problem for you, though. Could you do me a favor and jot down some notes about what you encounter out there? It could help a great deal towards understanding what we're fighting."}
d[58476]={de="All of the mogu clans are formidable, to be sure, but it is the Zan-Tien that pose the most direct threat to the Golden Lotus. Even now, their numbers are amassing outside the Golden Pagoda. Many of our warriors are fresh-faced and inexperienced. They would not withstand a mogu assault for long. An experienced {class} like you could serve to slow them down significantly. Care to help?"}
d[58477]={de="The Dokani see themselves fit to wield the ancient magic of anima, but their golems and manifestations are but a fraction of anima's true power. Liberate them of their prized substance, so that the Rajani may put it to better use."}
d[58478]={de="When the warring clans came into the Vale, the Baruk deigned themselves worthy to lay claim to the ancient grounds of Guo-Lai. They are not. Show these usurpers their place, and you may earn a modicum of favor with the Rajani."}
d[58595]={de="In ages past, the black obelisks of the Old Gods would herald the coming of their forces. The dark conjurers among the k'thir and n'raqi would utilize these monuments to establish footholds in our world and usher in more of the Old Gods' minions. Today, we see these very same obelisks littering the battlefields. So long as they stand, N'Zoth's forces will be without end. Make sure they do not."}
d[58740]={de="Where the Zan-Tien march, the warserpents are sure to follow. I cannot stress to you enough how dangerous these beasts are. It is a shame to see them subjugated by the mogu, but we cannot afford to let them run rampant. I need you to put them down before they can wreak havoc on our lines."}
d[58741]={de="One problem with waging war against other mogu is that weapons dull and break very quickly when used against foes of stone and metal. Being the sole blacksmith among the Rajani, it is sometimes difficult to keep up with our warriors needs. If you come across any weapons in your battles with the mogu, I'm sure I could put them to good use."}
d[58754]={de="It is clear that Shek'zara is fully committed to this invasion. Our scouts have spotted some of her greatest champions among the battlefield. Any one of these mantid could prove too much for the soldiers of the Golden Lotus to overcome. We must hunt them down and eliminate them ourselves. Are you in?"}
d[58755]={de="The invading mantid have been making off with the Golden Lotus' supplies lately. They're probably hoping they can starve us out. Well, they may be right if we can't get some of our supplies back. While you're taking the fight to the swarm, keep an eye out for anywhere they might have stashed our supplies. You'd be doing the Golden Lotus a big favor if you could recover some."}
d[58757]={de="During a swarm, the mantid send their youngest in great numbers against the enemy to test their mettle. Those who survive join the swarm as true warriors of the mantid. We should do our best to ensure that they don't make it through this test."}
d[58758]={de="The last mantid swarm is still very fresh in the memory of the Golden Lotus. Prior to the advancement of the swarm, the mantid would send their massive kunchong to soften up the defenders' lines. It would seem their tactics have not changed. We must stop those kunchong if the Golden Lotus hope to mount a defensive against the swarm. I'm counting on you to strike them down."}
d[58759]={de="The Zara'thik are the empress' elite guard. Empowered with plundered Azerite, they will stop at nothing short of absolute conquest of all of Pandaria. If we allow them to advance past the Serpent's spine, the Golden Lotus will be no match for them. Stop them at the wall, {class}."}
d[58760]={de="The mantid are frail and easily broken, but the amber blades they wield are formidable. With a bit of work, they could be reshaped into something suitable for the mogu. Bring them to me, and I can see about repurposing them to service the Rajani."}
d[58762]={de="There's something different about this mantid swarm. Instead of just killing everything in sight like the mantid usually do, they've taken to capturing our defenders and holding them alive. I really don't want to know what they have in store for the captives. Why don't you go rescue them so we don't have to find out?"}
d[58763]={de="The mantid use amber in nearly all aspects of their lives, from the structures they live in to the weapons they wield. Of course, I'm more interested in the latter. If we can deprive the mantid of their materials, we will deprive them of their means to create implements of war. Find where they keep their amber and make sure they are unable to use it."}
d[58764]={de="The brazen mantid think they've already won. Even now, they fly banners along the Serpent's Spine, announcing their dominance. They must learn that Pandaria belongs to the pandaren. Burn their banners down."}
d[58776]={de="The aqir are multiplying faster than we can put them down. If this pace continues, we will be outnumbered before long. The only way to slow down their assault is to attack their hives directly and destroy their eggs, but we have been unsuccessful in doing so. That's why I wish to conscript your services. Will you help?"}
d[58777]={de="<Zahra stomps on a slimy, slug-like creature as you approach.> You see that? Doesn't look like much, but believe it or not, those bugs grow out of these things. They're all over the places the aqir have taken over, feeding off of our dead and growing into these monstrosities. If you happen to see any of them, do the world a favor and take your boot to 'em."}
d[58778]={de="Morale's been down at the camp lately. Funny how getting chewed on by some bugs can spoil the mood of a place. I've got an idea to perk the troops back up, though. We need a trophy! See if you can get me the head of one of those big tanky-looking ones so we can put it on display to show these bugs that we mean business! Just try to make sure it's not too mangled, okay?"}
d[58779]={de="I'd like to see if we can get some more of these flyers in the air to drive back the aqir, but it's nearly impossible to get back to the Obelisk of the Sun with all these bugs in the air. I think we're going to have to thin them out on the ground before we can hope to gain aerial superiority. Can I count on you to lend a hand?"}
d[58780]={de="The aqir that have assaulted our camp seem to mainly consist of their shock troops. However, our scouts who dare venture behind their lines have spotted a different kind of creature -- tall and thin, wielding dangerous void magic. My instinct tells me that these creatures are the leaders behind this invasion. They should be seen as targets of opportunity, and cut down wherever they're met. Are you up to the task?"}
d[58781]={de="The Aqir threaten the livelihood of the Wastewanders with each passing day, but I have heard of greater terrors that have been unearthed with them. Our fighters are able, but I fear what might happen if one of these ancient terrors falls upon us. I know that you have experience putting down great foes. I would like to ask you to do the same for us. After all, we can hardly help protect the forge if we've been decimated by some long-buried monster."}
d[58782]={de="The invading aqir forced the Wastewanders to flee many of our settlements in Uldum. In our haste to escape, much was left behind. I understand you intend to take the fight to the beasts. While you're there, could you keep an eye out for any of the supplies we had to leave behind? You can keep anything of use to you, of course."}
d[58801]={de="<As your approach the idol, the dark shards you carry appear to melt into your hand. You are immediately overcome with unspeakable anguish. It quickly gives way to feelings of joy, serenity, and an overwhelming desire to... kill. A hissing voice creeps into your mind.> My faithful servant. I will grant you but a small taste of my unimaginable power, all I ask in return is that you complete one simple task. Kill any who would oppose me, spare no one. Do not fail me..."}
d[58805]={de="The egg is doing well, but we're going to need more of those void crystals to keep it healthy. Could you go out and gather some?"}
d[58831]={de="It looks like our little friend is anxious and ready to practice more combat. Would you care to show him the ropes?"}
d[58858]={de="Our little guy is getting hungry again. Could you pick him up a quick bite to eat?"}
d[58879]={de="<Sniffs curiously in the general direction of your backpack, eyeing it intently.>"}
d[58904]={de="<You feel the pull of something dark and inhuman on your mind, it's writhing tendrils digging in, tugging at your sanity. You feel compelled to collect more shards... all of them.>"}
d[59772]={de="The Cult of the Damned continue their work within the halls of Aldur'thar. Infiltrate their chambers and destroy their research. It may not stop them, but it will buy us valuable time."}
d[59782]={de="Though Deathspeaker Kharos has long since been slain, the cultists in the nearby mountains continue his nefarious work. Clearly emboldened by the Scourge's resurgence and the rift in the sky, they once again kidnap our crusaders and perform their abhorrent alchemical experiments. Go forth and purge those fanatics from their camp."}
d[59783]={de="Those damned cultists are relentless! They caught us off guard and managed to drag a few of our crusaders back to their camp. Light only knows what they're doing to them up there... Word is you're quite capable of holding your own. Our numbers are stretched thin enough as it is... if you could rescue the captives, we'd be in your debt. You can find the cultists lurking up in their mountain camp."}
d[59828]={de="Dear Maw Walker... my friend... you're going to lose. Everyone knows you can't compete in the arena. The entire Challenger's Promenade knows it, the brokers in Oribos know it, even Zo'umlo knows it. I've brought in a special challenger just to prove the point. Face Ti'or in the Theater of Pain and prove us wrong... or prove us right. We will be betting, so don't disappoint."}
d[59838]={de="The Scourge's war machines make it exceedingly difficult for us to gain ground. They must be our top priority. Though they are well protected, we must destroy them if we are to clear a path for our ground forces and grant them an opportunity to strike. Plant these charges underneath the war machines and then clear the area."}
d[59839]={de="Where some see a problem, I see an opportunity. What this Scourge fiasco calls for is a creative solution! Behold--my \"secret weapon\"! Controlled by none other than my Carefully Constructed Control Device, or C.C.C.D. for short! Hmm, that name might need a little work. You're the first to see it, so that means you'll be the first to test it. But don't worry, I'm pretty sure it's safe. Good luck!"}
d[59847]={de="The Scourge are assaulting our outpost! We must defend it at all costs! Slay as many of the fiends as you can!"}
d[59851]={de="The breath of a frost wyrm can freeze even its largest foes in an instant. Our forces, unfortunately, have experienced this firsthand. Their advance toward the citadel has come to a halt. I fear we may lose our foothold unless we act quickly. Take this potion and use it to free our forces from their frigid bonds. Light be with you."}
d[59863]={de="While everyone is busy fending off our enemies with swords and magic, how about we try something different. Behold, my latest invention--the Combat Nullifier 07-X! With this device, no enemy is truly your enemy any longer! Now, I haven't quite worked out the exact energy modulator calculations, but I am certain it works. Mostly. For now, we'll need to \"borrow\" some energy from our enemies in order to operate it. Go ahead. Charge it up and give it a whirl!"}
d[59878]={de="We cannot hope to hold this ground if frostwyrms strafe the skies above us. Cultists have been raising whelps from the dead nearby. The more of them we eliminate, the fewer monstrosities to breath deadly ice upon our forces. Put an end to their efforts."}
d[60153]={de="Come to pay old Marasmius a visit? I have a special task for you. One of my shoots has found a strange place, a place even I've never seen before. I'm not entirely sure what's in there or if it's even safe. But that's what my trusty mushroomancers are for! What do you say, {name}? Up for an adventure?"}
d[60175]={de="I'm a simple mushroom with simple pleasures, {name}. And what's simpler than a nice, hearty meal? Don't look so surprised. I need to eat just like anyone else! How else do you think I grew so big? Nice, tasty compost, that's how! Back in my day, I had the pick of Ardenweald for where to feed. Now, not so much. I've had a hankering for some of the loam that used to be around Tirna Noch. I haven't had shoots out there in a long time. Could you bring me some?"}
d[60283]={de="We have conjured Visectus to lead our attack, but we need your help to prepare it properly. We require more Anima-bound Wraps to strengthen the summons."}
d[60482]={de="After the destruction of our house, the spiders in this area become increasingly hostile. They expand their domain, and prey upon the few survivors that live here. There are weapons we could use to help protect ourselves, but they lie hidden within the Sightless Hold, webbed over by the weavers that inhabit it now. Journey to the hold, use my sightless vision to see the weapons and recover what you can."}
d[60505]={de="When our house fell in ruins, Manipulator Zalisar seized the opportunity to reform the house under his leadership. He found few followers and soon vanished into the ruins nearby. He has begun to manipulate the spiders and train them to be his soldiers. Spiders under his control have begun to prey upon our forces. We need to deal with this threat before it grows any worse. I need you eliminate Manipulator Zalisar and his spider forces."}
d[60732]={de="<The tortured embodiment of the soul before you burns with magmatic flame. Whatever purpose it was meant for here in the cauldron has since been served. The complete disregard for the remaining husk of this soul is unsettling. These efforts will continue if something isn't done. Send the inhabitants of Zovaal's Cauldron a message.>"}
d[60841]={de="Our forces are in danger, and the fault is my own. Believing that the surrounding area was safe, I sent a small team to secure the abandoned camp in the valley to the southwest. But our field reports were outdated or mistaken. The camp is a lost cause. We must now focus on rescuing those whom I assigned to it. Head for the camp. Do what you can to save our allies."}
d[61146]={de="As you know, shedding our memories of life can result in dangerous creatures known as manifestations. They have increased in number and strength as of late, but I believe we can find use for them yet. Manifestations carry great power within them--power we may purify and use in our own creations at the forge here. In making something positive out of such negativity, we do a noble act of service. Simply eliminate any you come across, and collect their essence. That is all."}
d[61156]={de="In times long past, Aspirants trained against the fauna of Bastion. The creation of the Centurions rendered such unstructured progression obsolete. The many flying denizens of this realm are known for their quills. They are light and sturdy, perfect for our purposes. Gather all that you can, please. Any flying creature shall suffice."}
d[61157]={de="The horned beasts of Bastion were once commonly used in aspirant training, but centurion sparring units have mostly taken their place. Over the past few eons, their numbers have grown and now must be culled. Their horns are critical components to our work. Many specimens are broken from use in battle--they will not suffice. You must be careful in collecting them. Face them, defeat them, and bring back their horns."}
d[61159]={de="All members of the Forsworn carry an insignia on their person at all times. We suspect they are imbued with the power of the Temple of Loyalty, bolstering their strength against us. Collect these insignias from their deceased forms. Strip them of this power, and we shall put it to better use in our own machinations. Such is the Archon's will, as it is ours."}
d[61166]={de="Centurions need lots of parts. But so do we! Kofi needs their metal. Can be from Centurions or the ground. Your choice! Not too damaged, ok? Hard to clean!"}
d[61182]={de="You know Twirlpetal flowers?! They spin around in the light! We need pollen. Only pollen if in bloom! Get a bunch! Flowers in golden fields. And they spin! Round and round!"}
d[61193]={de="Need Firstborne's Light! You know? Named after Archon! Always in water. Kofi's favorite! Shine big light when grown. And go to shore! Easy to see!"}
d[61196]={de="At times, even the most seasoned kyrian may have difficulty meditating. Recently, such problems have become increasingly common. There is a special draught crafted from our purest waters that can be used to focus the mind. I believe it may prove useful in our work here as well, perhaps as a catalyst for more potent reactions. Will you gather some? Move swiftly, for the liquid becomes unstable once removed from our sacred pools."}
d[61199]={de="Many battles here. Especially lately! Now weapons all over. Too many. We can use! Go to big battle places and grab them. We will use better!"}
d[61209]={de="Though we kyrian cease to be should we perish in battle here, there is much power within Bastion itself that can call forth echoes of our former brothers and sisters. These memories wander the roads. At times, they take on some purpose they served in their eternity here--crafting goods, guarding our sacred grounds, and the like. Take my lyre. Its ancient melody will dispel the memories, and in the process charge it with the residual energy of our realm."}
d[61875]={de="The Thistledrop is magnificent creature. The roots go deep into the earth where they drink of waters most ancient. With these waters they collect the very essence of the land into a drop of dew that enables our artisans to craft powerful armaments. Help us gather the dew and you will be well rewarded. Hurry, before it evaporates!"}
d[61950]={de="The supply of attuned anima is running low again. I'm surprised that we've managed to stretch our resources so far without a resupply. You've proven yourself proficient at tracking down what is needed, perhaps you could assist us once again? The runestags that roam Ardenweald's forests are particularly suffused with the power of the wilds, anima retrieved from them will be optimal for our needs. Good hunting!"}
d[61968]={de="For untold ages, the humble Ardenmoth has supplied the scales for the creation of armor for the Wild Hunt. Now, with our attention divided between the threats to the realm and the anima drought, it has become increasingly difficult for our foragers to find the perfect scales that we require. Only the scales of the highest quality are suitable. If you should obtain any in your travels and return with them, I shall ensure you are well rewarded."}
d[61985]={de="The land speaks to me, {name}. Ardenweald is a realm of cycles, but it has never faced an anima drought such as this. We will need the aid of all who reside here if we are to make it through this crisis. Many souls slumber within the forests and hills. If they can provide us some of their anima, we may be able to endure a little longer. Should you encounter any of the souls in your travels, please awaken them and send them to me."}
d[62057]={de="I've heard reports that the number of gorm sightings have risen greatly the past few days. Normally they're simple decomposers, playing their part in the great cycle, but in great numbers the gorm can be aggressive. If left unchecked, their ravenous hunger will cause untold destruction. The Wild Hunt has called for a gorm hunt. Meet your quota and you will be well-rewarded."}
d[62081]={de="Reports say that once again the spriggan are proving to be a nuisance, {name}. Word is that a bunch of them broke into the stores at the Heart of the Forest and made off with a huge store of animacones. Needless to say, we need those animacones back. The report says the spriggan group split up as they were making their escape, so any one you see is as likely to be carrying the animacones as the next. Good luck."}
d[62155]={de="Stone is a rare material in Ardenweald. Yet, I've heard tales that those who were masked by the Drust have small stones upon them. I'd like you to retrieve some of these stones for the Wild Hunt, so that we may better understand their link to our enemy. Face the masked and collect the stones from their deceased forms and I'll compensate you for your efforts. It's a gruesome task, but one that must be done."}
d[62160]={de="This grove needs something special, something to make it really stand out. I have a plan, but first I need flowers. Not just any flowers, but Night Lillies. They have a sweet scent that evokes starlit nights spent standing on a hilltop overlooking the majesty of the land. As you go exploring Ardenweald, look to the waterways for Night Lillies growing in the waterways and collect them. I will pay you for your efforts, of course."}
d[62188]={de="I require your aid on a... delicate matter, {name}. Starfly Wings form a vital ingredient for some of our creations and our supply is exhausted. They are tiny things, very fragile, and I am ill able to handle them delicately. Could you obtain the Starflies for me? They must be caught alive in order for their wings to not spoil and we desperately need them. I'll ensure that you are compensated for your time, of course."}
d[62224]={de="The Court of Night is akin to a thirsty flower, it quickly draws up its nutrients. If well supplied it will bloom and if its supply is depleted, it withers. Our roots are beginning to dry, we need more anima! I've sent workers out to place silk lined catchers along the roads and paths that cross Ardenweald. These catchers will collect a tiny bit of anima, not much but enough for what we need. Seek them out and return the Anima Infused Silk to us."}
d[62239]={de="<The weapon buzzes with a dark, static energy. Whatever this Mawsworn was testing, it appears to have been somewhat successful on the nearby rodents. Further investigation may yield additional information.>"}
d[62262]={de="Just as I was making progress on our alternative defense research, my spore samples ran dry! The mushrooms I was using can only be found in a particularly unpleasant location to the southeast. To collect an appropriately sized sample, you'll have to--how do I put this--feed them. Don't ask me why, but apparently, they mature fastest with a nice, rotting corpse nearby. Try luring a few undead to our fungal friends. That should give 'em all the nutrients they need to grow big and strong."}
d[62295]={de="The Scourge's rampant aggression has proven difficult to predict, even for us. By the time we knew they were upon us, it was too late. With our forces spread thin, we are left with what you see before you. Enter the vault. Slay our enemies where they stand. Soon the Shadow Vault will be ours once more."}
d[62296]={de="Come to pay old Marasmius a visit? I have a special task for you. One of my shoots has found a strange place, a place even I've never seen before. I'm not entirely sure what's in there or if it's even safe. But that's what my trusty mushroomancers are for! What do you say, {name}? Up for an adventure?"}
d[62362]={de="The living slime within Maldraxxus naturally produces a powerful catalyst used in many of the House of Eyes's poisons. There is always a need for the substance. It would be of great help if you could retrieve some for us."}
d[62363]={de="The stronger members of the House of the Chosen tend to take a fairly specific form. No doubt you've seen the larger warriors in the house? They are the greatest threat in their collective force. Thin them out."}
d[62364]={de="Necromancers and liches often use powerful tomes to assist in their rituals. Now that the House of Rituals has expanded their reach, the tomes can be found anywhere where their members are active. Find these books and destroy them. It won't end their vile experiments but it should at least delay them."}
d[62365]={de="What better way to stop our enemies in their tracks than to use their own experiments against them? Lucky for us, some of our... friends have left a few samples unattended. And I know just where to test it... As menacing as they may be, those abominations down there are delicate creations. It would be a shame if you were to get your hands on some of their equipment and disrupt the process..."}
d[62382]={de="Come to pay old Marasmius a visit? I have a special task for you. One of my shoots has found a strange place, a place even I've never seen before. I'm not entirely sure what's in there or if it's even safe. But that's what my trusty mushroomancers are for! What do you say, {name}? Up for an adventure?"}
d[62390]={de="I am acquainted with a few fleshcrafters who work outside of the House of Constructs. If we can find reagents for them, they can supply our war effort with constructs. The House of Constructs has plenty of excess body parts. Find them and bring them back here."}
d[62401]={de="The Lich King's minions once carried scourgestones given to them by their dark master. New ones have been found on the corpses of the undead. We do not know their purpose... but they have been touched by even more sinister magic. As you slay the Scourge across Icecrown, keep your eyes open for such stones. If you bring them back to me, I shall turn them over to the confessors for study."}
d[62403]={de="The boars around Maldraxxus have a peculiar trait. Their tusks absorb liquid. Depending on where it has been, these bones may contain a powerful compound of poisons or other alchemical rarities. It takes a trained eye to tell what the bone is made of, so just bring back a large amount of them. From there I will see if any of them are valuable."}
d[62453]={de="Come to pay old Marasmius a visit? I have a special task for you. One of my shoots has found a strange place, a place even I've never seen before. I'm not entirely sure what's in there or if it's even safe. But that's what my trusty mushroomancers are for! What do you say, {name}? Up for an adventure?"}
d[62465]={de="Ah, you're just in time. I've made quite the discovery. I've managed to make a connection even further out than I ever have before. How did I do it, you ask? Hard work, that's how! But you knew that. You're almost as hardworking as I am. That's what you're here for! Up for an even more exciting adventure?"}
d[62473]={de="These damn Scourge make me sick! <Brollen spits on the ground.> They're only good fer one thing--bein' dead! Head tae the valley southwest o' here. Plenty o' gear fer the pickin' over there! Gather up what ye can. I'll make do with what ye find."}
d[62484]={de="We received an... unusual delivery recently. I'm still in a bit of shock. Some sort of flying contraption released a huge crate just overhead, parachute and all. If it weren't for the wind it would have landed nearby. Instead, it drifted down the hill below. They left a note too. It would have been lost had it not been wrapped around a sizeable rock. <Darkrider Arly massages a spot on her forehead.> I don't know what it is, but if it'll help clear out the area, I'm all for it."}
d[62553]={de="The Scourge continue to replenish their weapons of war from blighted grounds. Stopping their workers slows their production, but a decisive blow to their stockpiles would be far more effective. Take these and head to the area southeast of here. Plant the bombs, then make a quick exit. Weakening their supply lines should provide us ample time to retaliate."}
d[62563]={de="Gorgantus just won't give up! We've defeated her several times already, but the scavengers salvage the body, fix her up and send her right back in here! She thinks this time she will defeat us... prove her wrong."}
d[62584]={de="This forward camp relies heavily on our supply line from the tournament grounds. A recent shipment was attacked while in transit through the valley below us. Salvage what you can, and if possible, eliminate the threat so this does not happen again."}
d[62606]={de="Ah, just the mushroomancer I wanted to see! Mind getting me some clay? There's all kinds of different soil, you know. It's not all just dirt! And clay... clay is something special. You ever try growing through clay? Oh, I guess not. It's hard work to break down, but once you do the flavor is incomparable! My roots are looking forward to the challenge. Blackthorn Grove has a particularly bitter and complex clay that is just what I'm craving. I'm sure they won't mind if you ask them for some."}
d[62607]={de="Well, hello there! Fancy helping me out today? You ever been to Shimmerbough? Ever wonder why it's called that? I was there when it was named, you know. Lots of people think it's the trees or the water, and they're right. But the secret to the shimmering is in the silt. The soil soaks and gains excess anima from the water, until the ground itself practically sparkles. I could really go for some shimmersilt right now. Would you let an old mushroom relive his youth?"}
d[62608]={de="So nice to see you again. I've got a special request for you. The Winter Queen herself used to tend directly to groves, in the early times. Everything she touched burst with life and power. Even the ground she walked on. Over time, the Queen's Garden came to be known as the Garden of Night, for the Queen had not tended to her garden in so long. But the ground is still potent with her power. It's the finest meal I've ever had. I know this is indulgent, but you and I both know I deserve it!"}
d[62610]={de="<Marasmius sighs.> They're at it again, up in the Stalks. Seems like we didn't give them enough of a thrashing the first time, eh? What say you and I team up again and teach those younglings a lesson they won't forget? Let me know when you're ready and we'll get 'em, just like before!"}
d[62611]={de="Those masked fiends have taken over Heartwood Grove, and I mean to stop their plans. Heartwood Grove was so beautiful before. And now, it's... No matter. We're going to fix this, you and me. Right now. Come, join me in battle. We'll give those monsters a thrashing that will make their masters think twice before desecrating that sacred place again!"}
d[62614]={de="I hope you're ready to fight. The Drust are bolstering their forces in Eventide Grove. Most of Ardenweald doesn't remember them, but I do. You have to completely root them out to be rid of their presence, or they'll grow right back, tougher than ever. Come with me. We're going to exterminate every last one of them. Let me know when you're ready."}
d[62615]={de="Bad news from the Gossamer Cliffs. We need to help. The varmints terrorizing the poor silk striders have become more cruel and aggressive lately. The silk striders are important to Ardenweald; more important than almost anyone else knows. We can't lose any more. Let me know when you're ready to go and we'll scare those gits away for good!"}
d[63031]={de="<This shard of crystal appears to have broken off of one of the massive crystalline structures throughout the area. It thrums with untapped energy. Ve'nari would likely be interested in any of these shards you come across.>"}
d[63039]={de="<Corpses of Ebon Blade knights litter the Crucible of the Damned, displaying the aftermath of your first foray into this desolate place. Their sacrifice should not be forgotten.>"}
d[63043]={de="The traps... they didn't affect us before. Too many souls... escaping. They... made new traps... tear apart fleeing souls... ...too late for me. Destroy... so others might escape!"}
d[63047]={de="<The chains here are carved with domination runes, imbuing them with the magic needed to subdue the most powerful of the Mawsworn's prisoners. No doubt Ve'nari could find some use in studying these runes.>"}
d[63050]={de="<The runesmiths have imbued this ingot with an enchantment that causes it to burn with inextinguishable flames. It is likely that this metal is used to empower the Mawsworn protectors of Zovaal's Cauldron. Bringing some samples of this ore to Ve'nari could aid her attempts at unlocking the Jailer's secrets.>"}
d[63062]={de="<A broker device has been abandoned here. It seems like it was being used to siphon energy from rifts of soul energy that have erupted in the area. The brokers surely would not have sought to harness this energy if it didn't have a use. Perhaps you should finish what they started.>"}
d[63069]={de="<It looks like this broker was gathering information before he met his unfortunate end. Ve'nari would likely be very interested in what he found. Unfortunately, his notes look to have been scattered far and wide by the local beasts.>"}
d[63072]={de="<The rock columns in this area are teeming with veins of a glowing, otherworldly metal. The Mawsworn have employed souls to mine it, but it looks like they didn't last long. Ve'nari could certainly find use for some of this ore, if you can manage to mine it.>"}
d[63100]={de="<The husk of this poor soul has been stripped of everything, down to near nonexistence. This suffering cannot continue. Save the others from their misery.>"}
d[63166]={de="The Mawsworn... torture and torment souls within Ruin's Cradle. I... barely escaped, but I'm afraid I won't last long. Their twisted rituals... breaking souls to serve as wretched shades. Spare them this fate!"}
d[63179]={de="Maw Walker! I am relieved to see you in this place. A dark sect of kyrian who have allied themselves with the Maw stole my brothers and sisters from their posts in Bastion. They turned us over to a foul sea witch, the likes of which I've never seen. This... Helya, I believe they called her... seems determined to break us so that we might also join her ranks. Please, if you can, save my brethren."}
d[63775]={de="The repositories of knowledge within Korthia have layers of security--for very good reasons. Each vault requires cryptographs in order to decode and disable the barriers. They are, for lack of a better term, the keys to every secret. Search outside the Vault for cryptographs stolen by the Mawsworn and return them to me. I will keep them, and the secrets they protect, safe."}
d[63778]={de="It breaks my heart to see another land so utterly obliterated. I can imagine how beautiful Korthia must have been, once. But we must not wallow in what we've lost. Like Ara'lon taught me: we don't have to stand still. We can choose to fight. You can help by taking anima back from those Mawsworn. We can put it to use, building up our own forces and defenses."}
d[63779]={de="{name}, we have to help the attendants of Korthia. They have lost so much, so suddenly. Nearby, in the Sanctuary of Guidance, they would take offerings and leave them at shrines. Since the mawsworn invaded, they haven't been able to enter the Sanctuary or retrieve their precious offerings. If you could collect the offerings and retrieve them. It might allow the attendants some semblance of their normal lives."}
d[63780]={de="Just thinking about how the Jailer's forces breached Ardenweald makes me so mad! And when I get mad, I get even. Or rather, I get your help with getting even! Slay those Mawsworn and bring back their emblems to show me how many you killed. I don't really care where you get them, as long as they come from those Maw jerks!"}
d[63781]={de="Which is more damaging to the enemy, destroying a contingent of their forces or interrupting their communications? Better yet, what if that communication allows you to best place your forces to ambush their reinforcements? I see you understand. There will be a Mawsworn lieutenant, Voxiferus, traveling from the Maw into Korthia, by way of the northern road. Find them, kill them, and bring me the battle plans."}
d[63782]={de="The Mawsworn have a myriad of magic users among their forces. Their magic is unknown to us and that makes it deadly. We need to learn what they are capable of to properly prepare a defense. My own curiosity about their methods and rituals is secondary. Hunt down these vile casters and bring me their grimoires."}
d[63783]={de="Our efforts here need a constant supply of troops, supplies, and anima. The last one is the hardest, for obvious reasons. But I've learned to be resourceful. Nearby there is a plentiful source of anima: the devourers that currently swarm the Sanctuary of Guidance. It's not as easy as beating it out of a soul, but it's just as effective, if you're strong enough. Are you?"}
d[63784]={de="{name}! How's things? We 'eard there was all kinds of interestin' stuff out 'ere. So, 'em sneakin' hoppers? Hard to see, innit? They've got 'emselves a shiny pelt as me 'n' the lads could use to stay out of sight, as it were. You know, avoid the bosses n' such. I need ya to capture a bundle of 'em. Gold's no object, just bring me the little pests alive."}
d[63785]={de="The onslaught from Zovaal's forces continues to devastate these lands. We must send them a message. Show them we will not back down, {name}. The might of Ardenweald stands with you."}
d[63786]={de="The skies over Korthia are a dangerous place. Not only do the Mawsworn threaten our forces; the native creatures are also openly hostile. We must keep the skies safe for our own winged allies and beasts. The source of the native flyers is the Windswept Aerie. Go there and clear the aerie of aggressive creatures. Then, we shall have aerial supremacy."}
d[63787]={de="My Eyes tell me that the Mauler's Outlook is near the newly formed road from the Maw into Korthia. It would provide a strategic and tactical advantage. Unfortunately, the area is overrun with shardhides. If we can secure the area, it will provide us with a clear path to the west, as well as a point of observation to monitor the Jailer's forces."}
d[63788]={de="The attendant's home has been destroyed by the Jailer, but we can help them in this trying time. Nearby is the Sanctuary of Guidance. They speak of it with reverence and great sadness. It is a place they go to pray and seek truth. It's currently infested with devourers. Clear out the devourers, so they may once more seek solace in their rituals and prayers."}
d[63789]={de="We cannot allow the mawsworn a foothold so close to our own encampment. The attendants say they keep this place hidden from eyes, but I will not rest easy while I can see them. Enter the Scholar's Den and cleanse the Jailer's forces from it."}
d[63790]={de="A powerful dreadlord named Lord Azzorak is hampering the efforts of the Cartel in Korthia. Anyone who exterminates this evil will be rewarded. Use caution. Azzorak is a powerful foe. You may require several allies to slay him."}
d[63791]={de="A spike-armored Mawsworn named Valdinar the Curseborn is hampering the efforts of the Cartel in Korthia. Anyone who exterminates this evil will be rewarded. Use caution. Valdinar is a powerful foe. You may require several allies to defeat him."}
d[63792]={de="A nefarious Maw magus named Nocturnus the Unraveler is hampering the efforts of the Cartel in Korthia. Anyone who exterminates this evil will be rewarded. Use caution. Nocturnus is a powerful foe. You may require several allies to defeat him."}
d[63793]={de="A winged Mawsworn named Ensydius the Defiler is hampering the efforts of the Cartel in Korthia. Anyone who exterminates this evil will be rewarded. Use caution. Ensydius is a powerful foe. You may require several allies to defeat him."}
d[63794]={de="New lands bring new opportunity. We will provide a quantity of valuables to any interested party in return for a substantial amount of devourer blood, preferably the goliath kind. Faint-hearted collectors need not bother. Please bring this sample to Ta'nasi in Keeper's Respite."}
d[63934]={de="Greetings, mortal! I am on a mission to deliver messages to our allies here in exciting Korthia. However, I was unable to complete my task. The messages I was programmed to transport were stolen by Mawsworn, and then incorrectly stored all over the ground. Would you collect the messages and return them to me? I will then see them delivered to their intended recipients. Thank you!"}
d[63935]={de="Korthia. A sister forest, stricken. But in the throes of destruction, there is still hope. Gather the anima, and build anew."}
d[63936]={de="Sika has idea! Devourers... devour. They eat anything! So they eat anima, too. If we take anima from devourers, then that anima is ours!"}
d[63937]={de="There's tons of interesting things to kill out here! Bears, birds, mawsworn, and gromits! Let's start with the gromits shall we? Go slaughter the fierce gromits in the Mauler's Outlook and bring me their FANGS! I can always use more teeth."}
d[63950]={de="These lands are not well known yet by my hunters, but we have discovered formidable beasts that reside here. Among these are the Razorwing: vicious predators with terrible talons... and the temper of a vorkai. <Herne grins fiercely.> Bring me some of their talons to help teach our newest hunters about the kinds of beasts they will face."}
d[63955]={de="Ah, Korthia. What secrets will be revealed? My associates have been hard at work, seeking to discover and procure various small items of interest throughout this broken land. Nothing of great importance, I assure you. They have secured those items in designated drop boxes, and those now await pickup outside of the Vault. Don't worry, they are locked with an impenetrable seal to protect both the contents and the deliverer. Bring those sealed containers to me, and I will reward you handsomely."}
d[63959]={de="Greetings, Maw Walker, a moment of your time? As you no doubt know, my cartel has quietly spread observational devices all across Korthia. But that data is no good to us if it is not retrieved. Which is where you come in. The Sanctuary of Guidance records should be ready to collect. You won't see the devices themselves, but the data will appear to you as a bright orb. Bring those data to me, and I will reward you handsomely."}
d[63963]={de="New lands bring new opportunity. To any interested party, we will provide a quantity of valuables in return for a piece of heavily spiked hide from the beast known as Ripmaul. Faint-hearted collectors need not bother. Please bring this sample to Ta'nasi in Keeper's Respite."}
d[63964]={de="New lands bring new opportunity. To any interested party, we will provide a quantity of valuables in return for an intact boney beak from the beast known as Grimtalon. Faint-hearted collectors need not bother. Please bring this sample to Ta'nasi in Keeper's Respite."}
d[63965]={de="I'm amazed by the wildlife here in Korthia! So many interesting creatures... Say, you know those flying beasts with the claws, the Razorwing? They sometimes knock their eggs out of their nests, and then they completely ignore them! If you find any abandoned eggs, could you bring them to me? Gently, of course. I wonder if they can be raised to be friendly? If not, well, it wouldn't be the first time I've had my antennae chewed on."}
d[63989]={de="Apprentice! I've been looking for you. Kevin has been such a wonderful helper in our experiments, I'd like to train my other oozes to be able to assist as well! Can you take Plaguey with you and test their ability to infect organic life forms?"}
d[64015]={de="All these mawsworn have got me excited for some slaughter! I've got a plan that probably won't end in you dying. Are you in?"}
d[64018]={de="The campaign continues, {name}. The Stone Legion is here to turn the tide of battle. First, we must deliver supplies to our allies. The broken land of Korthia means we are the only ones who can keep our troops supplied. Second, we must deal with the mawsworn and the devourers. I have a very simple strategy. We are going to drop anima onto the mawsworn. That will attract the devourers to attack. Either they kill the mawsworn, or the mawsworn kills them. Regardless, we win."}
d[64040]={de="The mawsworn continue to engage our forces at the Vault. There are heavy casualties on both sides. We must help! Take this and restore any wounded covenant allies you find. Mikanikos helped me create it. It runs on anima and should help patch up anyone. Even the Stoneborn or Maldraxxi."}
d[64043]={de="There are too many wounded on the battlefield! Not everyone can 'bash it and make better.' We need more healers. You: take my device and get our wounded back on their feet!"}
d[64065]={de="Korthia is an odd place. The wildlife here is different, likely due to years of exposure to the Vault and everything it contains. Are you ready to try some experiments? We'll need a good stock of reagents first. Near the Seeker's Quorum, you should be able to find shardhides, gromits, and razorwings. Watch out for their needles!"}
d[64070]={de="Our army always need more weapons, armor, and troops. Always. We're getting reinforcements, but I can't keep everyone properly armed at this rate. Especially without a full forge and assistants. We'll have to make do with the next best thing. I need you to go get me any kind of scrap metal from the Mawsworn you can find. I'll figure out how to turn it into usable weapons."}
d[64080]={de="I can hear the wings of the Mawsworn in the sky up above, taunting us. But a bird in the hand can be crushed. Take my spear and prove your aim. Pull a few down and smite them. Be sure to use the spear. Do not traipse among them so that they will chase you back down to the ground. That's not the point. I want to see you drag them out of the sky."}
d[64089]={de="How delightful! What a lovely little spot of nature. Have you tried the local brews? Perhaps a nice herbal tea? No? Well, let's try it together! Search about this place and bring back any herbs that look... interesting. A good spot of tea, and then we shall get to work. I'll wait here."}
d[64101]={de="I came here to observe the actions of those from Revendreth. However I have been met with news that concerns me. {name}, the attendants tell me that they stored anima in canisters and that anima is being looted, by our own people. That's not how this should be done. Can I entrust you to retrieve the anima, so I might see it returned to its proper place?"}
d[64103]={de="{name}. Here we are again, fighting alongside each other to protect the Shadowlands. We're waging a losing war, but we might be able to turn the tide. I need you to seek out some very specific commanders of the Mawsworn forces. In every army, there's good commanders and bad ones. By taking out the good ones, only the bad ones advance, weakening the force as a whole. Our Eyes have brought us the names. Now I just need you to kill them."}
d[64104]={de="The wildlife of Korthia have been through so much. Some of them can't seem to find enough to eat. I've saved some extra food that we can share with them. But I'm worried that they might be too shy to trust us, and I don't blame them! Here. Take these treats and see if you can get close enough to them to feed them properly. Even small creatures are so important."}
d[64129]={de="Ever since I joined the Wild Hunt I've learned so much about how to fight and how to defend the realms. I admit I'm still learning. But I am so glad to be learning alongside you, and my runestag friend, Aldermeigh. Aldermeigh is being trained to charge into battle with the bravery of a vorkai, but he needs practice. Will you take him out for a ride, and mow down all the Mawsworn you can?"}
d[64166]={de="When the Jailer snared Korthia and dragged it toward the Maw, he destroyed so much in this place. Not only mountains and buildings, but the people, too. Those people had lives, hopes, memories. I have to think that they can't all be gone, and we might be able to save something of them that lingers. Here, take some of my power. See if you can collect those memories. Bring them to me, and I'll keep them safe. No one should be forgotten."}
d[64194]={de="As Forgelite Prime, I always work to make something better! But largest centurions, they are much too large to bring to Korthia. This, I fix. Here is Atleos, field colossus prototype. Vanguard of the Kyrian! It needs testing. More testing. Must be perfect against a powerful opponent. Go, take Atleos and defeat a great Maw beast! Press all the buttons!"}
d[64240]={de="We've engaged in a heavy battle at the entrance to the Vault of Secrets! Our forces could use some reinforcement. Please, guide my fellow Ascended to give support to our fighters there. The fighters on the ground can handle the clean-up, but they need shields and healing. Good luck!"}
d[64271]={de="Ah, {name}. I have a matter to discuss with you. But not here. <Nadjia eyes the other denizens of Keeper's Respite suspiciously.> Meet me where the road enters Korthia from the Maw and I will explain."}
d[64282]={de="You continue to surprise me Maw Walker, your presence here is most unexpected! Since we are both here, I believe we should work together. The Jailer has a vault full of valuables, somewhere in this rift. Locate it for me, or bring it here to be opened and we'll share the wealth together!"}
d[64430]={de="It seems Tubbins and Gubbins have gone off somewhere. I do worry about the two of them. Be a dear and check on them. One never knows what shenanigans they might be up to. I last saw them speaking with one of the faeries from Ardenweald. They were discussing the fine art of tea making."}
d[64432]={de="{name}, the scrap metal we've been recovering has some interesting properties. I have come to believe the mawsworn are imbuing their armor and increasing its durability. Take this lightning rod. First, you will need to get struck by lightning. Don't make that face. You'll be fine. But, you need to also be grounded on mawsworn metal. The large chains embedded in Korthia, near the Windswept Aerie should work. Once you are... ah... energized, I will send a tauralus, Borrhas, to carry you into battle."}
d[64579]={de="The large metal spheres that litter the landscape of Zereth Mortis are spent forges, discarded during the creation process. These empty metal husks still contain residual materials of creation that may be useful to us. Use my Forge-Tap near these metal spheres to harvest any Remnant Neomotes. You may also find other useful proto-materials!"}
d[64592]={de="The outsiders have disrupted the sands. We cannot reach the terraforming records we need in order to collect necessary historical information. Will you assist us? Help Mai Obet collect historical records in the Endless Sands."}
d[64717]={de="The large metal spheres that litter the landscape of Zereth Mortis are spent forges, discarded during the creation process. The spheres near the Forge of Afterlives contain trace amounts of materials unique to that location. I have modified my Forge-Tap to harvest those materials. Use it near the forges I have identified. The rare Eidolic Fragments have the greatest chance to be found on the largest of Progenitor Forges."}
d[64783]={de="Simon says, \"Are you ready to dance?\" Step on in and show off your sweet moves, {class}. The rules are simple. Your opponent will perform a series of stylish moves, then you gotta match 'em. Earn enough accolades and then come back to ol' Simon. Just know that the more challenging the opponent, the more accolades you can earn. Simon says, \"Are you up for the challenge?\""}
d[64785]={de="Since our arrival here the Untamed Verdure has been a mystery waiting to be solved. The lush foliage of the area grows on everything as the creatures run amok without purpose. There could be valuable research data to be obtained from these creatures. Use a Containment Trap to subdue the elemental creatures. Once subdued, examine them for research data."}
d[64850]={de="I've heard of you, the Maw Walker! You must know of me, the legendary Ve'nish. I am here to find great treasures within Torghast with the aid of my box. I can see you admiring it. Perhaps we can work together. Why don't you go into Torghast ahead of me to scout ahead? I shall even reward you for anything you discover within."}
d[64852]={de="<Firim could make use of this item>"}
d[64854]={de="The wildlife of Zereth Mortis are attracted to the frenetic creation energy that flows throughout the land. When the wildlife finds something charged with that energy... they eat it! The Mawsworn Cryptoseers have become aware of this and are attempting to find such wildlife to extract any remnants of that energy. Eliminate the Cryptoseers, and use the Containment Trap to subdue and examine the wildlife for our research."}
d[64860]={de="<Firim could make use of this item>"}
d[64964]={de="The presence of the Jailer's forces at Provis Strata have been causing untold damage to the region. If left unchecked, we will lose all knowledge in the area. One of our kin has prepared some automa to deal with the Mawsworn. Meet with them, and fight back against those who would disrespect Zereth Mortis in this manner."}
d[64977]={de="One of the remarkable things we have found about these lands is that they seem to be adaptive and changing, even as ancient as they are. Things are not stationary. In the depths of the Nexus of Actualization there is a forge that appears made to test these various designs, and to learn. These creatures may one day be used to defend Zereth Mortis from threats, so you should test their effectiveness where possible. Go there, challenge what the forge creates and report back to me."}
d[65072]={de="Rana's discovery of Progenitor relics at the Ageless Shards has created quite a stir among the Enlightened. These relics predate our earlier discoveries, and through them we may gain a deeper understanding of the workings of Zereth Mortis. Rana is collecting the relics, but I fear she is in danger. Agents of Cartel Xy have been spotted in the area, and will likely attempt to steal the relics. Please travel to the Ageless Shards, and help Rana collect the relics."}
d[65096]={de="We have obtained a wealth of information from relics discovered at the Ageless Shards. The Mawsworn are aware of our discoveries, and are trying to stop us. They have placed traps around the area to block access to the relics. We cannot allow the Jailer to cut off our access to those relics. Please eliminate this Mawsworn threat, and recover as many relics as possible."}
d[65142]={de="To aid in my studies, I have used a network of travel portals to install monitoring devices all over Zereth Mortis. My devices have been quite successful at collecting large amounts of research data. It's time now to collect the data they have obtained. Use my portal network to locate my Prying Eyes and collect any data they have gathered. I'll give you a portal initiator as well, allowing you to re-enter the portal network, incase you find yourself lost!"}
d[65177]={de="We never know when something new may emerge from the confluence of creation and energy. The Catalyst Gardens have blossomed with a new crop of fruit. Their seeds may have special properties, and we wish to understand them. Please gather what you can find, and make the gardens safer for the future."}
d[65226]={de="When the Mawsworn came to Zereth Mortis, they brought mawrats with them! A swarm of their mawrats overran my cave, making off with many of our research items! Rana is assembling a team to help recover the items. Meet up with her and aid in the effort."}
d[65255]={de="The forces of Zovaal have been spreading their malign influence into the natural life within Provis Fauna. With the rate of their corruption, attempting to cleanse them one by one would be ill advised. Instead, we can just return their energies into the systems of Zereth Mortis to be used to create new fauna. Use this orb, let it absorb their energy as they die, and then cleanse it once it has been charged."}
d[65256]={de="The endemic poultrids of Zereth Mortis have been influenced in an unseemly way by all these invaders. Use this device on the ones that have malfunctioned. Otherwise, they will do too much damage to the land."}
d[65264]={de="Devourers have disrupted the avians nesting at Provis Esper. This may be our last chance to examine them before they become tainted, like the others. Capture several of the avians at Provis Esper and return them to Pilgrim Arizh for relocation and study. Deal with any problems that get in your way."}
d[65265]={de="Much has been lost to the invading forces, those that came with destruction in their hearts. We cannot preserve this land as the First Ones intended if the Mawsworn are allowed to pulverize all remnants of their knowledge. See what you can recover from the sands of Provis Strata."}
d[65268]={de="The vespoids of the region use debris in the area to form the core of their nests. While this is normally something we'd allow them to naturally do, they've started taking some of the relics we were studying. I have a device that should hopefully allow for the removal of such relics from their hives without damaging the core structure. Use it to retrieve these relics."}
d[65269]={de="The situation in the Catalyst Gardens is troubling. But most troubling of all is that we do not know more. If we had an understanding of the changing levels of energy emitted by the Creation Catalyst, we could make better decisions as to how to proceed. Take these sensors. Place them below the catalyst at the locations marked upon your map."}
d[65325]={de="The creatures of Untamed Verdure are ingesting everything in sight. They have consumed our Compilation Nodule, and the Composition Motes needed for compilation. We Jiro require these resources. This area is too hazardous for unprotected Jiro operation. Please help us reclaim our resources. Mai Obet will assist you."}
d[65326]={de="Automa need assistance to operate properly. We fulfill this purpose, but outsiders have caused too many interruptions. We cannot properly address them all. Please assist Mai Obet in inspecting and reviewing the performance of the automa."}
d[65362]={de="Enemies of Zereth Mortis wear the guise of productive automa. They do not complete any desired tasks. Scan the automa to reveal enemy threats, then eliminate them. Mai Obet shall assist."}
d[65363]={de="Enemies have attacked the jiro and severed them from the circle. The jiro are no longer stable. They are a danger to the order of things. They must be removed."}
d[65364]={de="The outsiders have disrupted the tasks and purpose of the jiro. We cannot allow this to continue. We will empower a larger jiro to help combat these threats. Jiro Prime will destroy the enemies that threaten Zereth Mortis. Help direct Jiro Prime to resolve our crisis."}
d[65445]={de="Devourers are consuming neomotes. We need neomotes for necessary creation work. Without them, we are unable to complete our work. Eliminate the devourers and retrieve the neomotes."}
d[65784]={de="To the northeast, there are a system of otter burrows along the bank. Some of the otters there are blessed by the river to grow to magnificent sizes. I will not have you hunting these blessings out of respect. Instead you will bring them back here, alive, so that we may treat them with the reverence they deserve."}
d[65789]={de="The Mirewood contains key reagents often used to converse with the ancestors. Unfortunately, the Mudfin tribe swarms the area, making it difficult for us to forage the area. If you could gather some of the blooms within the marsh, along with some of the Mudfin's own resources, I would appreciate it."}
d[65792]={de="Toliqui has been claiming that just the other day she killed a rockfang without any assistance. Given our connected souls, I don't want to call her as a liar. So instead... I want to prove to her, and everyone else, that I'm the better half of our soul! The nearest rockfang quest is to the northeast - meet me there!"}
d[65796]={de="Our next path is through Nokhud territory. Historically, we have been at a tentative peace with their clan, but times have changed. If we do not act first, we leave ourselves open while we're vulnerable. My scouts have reported that one of their war leaders has been spotted near Dragonsmeet. Take the fight to her directly - do not let her gather the forces to assault us on the move."}
d[65798]={de="The Shikaar have formed an offensive line against the Nokhud to the north. While I do not like stooping to scavenging, it is unfortunately a necessary evil for our supplies. Brave the battlefield and return with weapons, and I will reward your efforts. If you could focus said efforts on the Nokhud side of the line, perhaps the ancestors will judge me less harshly."}
d[66241]={de="Fly through the checkpoint rings marking the course."}
d[66698]={de="One of our key resources is our argali herd. Every loss is felt deeply for the strength of our clan. A few of the argali have gotten separated and have wandered away from the herd. Our shepherds could use your assistance reclaiming them."}
d[66711]={de="Due to the nature of our clan, some resources are in short supply. We do not have the luxury of time to claim the land's metal resources. The late khan established multiple trade connections with a variety of individuals, and I see no reason to discontinue their services. The nearby bay contains buckets where we catch whelks - they're considered a delicacy for some of our neighbors. Bring a collection back to me for use in trade."}
