d[70210]={de="One tradition for the Aylaag as we stay at this camp is for our members to make the pilgrimage to the Eternal Kurgans to ask for journeys safe from that which plagued our ancestors. The presence of the Nokhud has made this pilgrimage perilous. If you do not mind, I would ask you would uphold our tradition for us."}
d[70279]={de="As you've no doubt seen, this land contains creatures which grow beyond their normal size. We consider these beasts as blessed by the gods of the wild, and they are often considered honorable targets for hunters to prove their strength. One of these beasts, which we call Karkidan, is nearby. I would be most impressed if you managed to take it down."}
d[70299]={de="I've heard words on the wind of outsiders allying with Clan Nokhud in an effort to defeat our dragon neighbors. These Primalists are a blight on the plains of our ancestors. Slay them, and bring me the cores of the elementals they command."}
d[70352]={de="You there, outsider! You have killed proto dragons before, yes? So it stands to reason that your experience combined with my hunting prowess, we can take down quite a few! There are springs around here that attract draconic beasts. Help me prove to my foolish other half that I am the better hunter."}
d[70438]={de="The fish could be biting better, don't you think? You know, that gives me an idea. Legend says these lakes and rivers did not always have fish. They say, these watering holes were stocked with fish when the dragons soaring overhead dropped them! Can you believe it? Maybe you and your drake could give it a try?"}
d[70450]={de="Hey there, friend. These here ottuks keep stealin' my catch! Personally, I'd blow 'em up, but our Tuskarr friends don't seem too keen on that action. I made this here Ottuk Deterent Device MK-SH4RK, but... I aint a great swimmer. You seem like you got the goods, why don't ya do us all a favor, activate the device, swimmy-swim around over there, and scare 'em off?"}
d[70526]={de="Fly through the checkpoint rings marking the course."}
d[70542]={de="Fly through the checkpoint rings marking the course."}
d[70701]={de="Some of the clan's argali have wandered away from our flock again. The ridge around us is too dangerous for our shepherds to search for them. It would be a great boon if you could take one of our bakar and bring back the argali. Our shepherds can point you in the right direction."}
d[70710]={de="Fly through the checkpoint rings marking the course."}
d[70711]={de="Fly through the checkpoint rings marking the course."}
d[70848]={de="<Exadria might want this.>"}
d[70990]={de="While most of our wool comes from our own argali flocks, we do sometimes need to pull from the land when the flock grows thin. The nearby plains are home to wild argali - they tend to be more temperamental than our clan's flock. If you could take this blade and attempt to shear their wool, it would be a great service to Aylaag."}
d[71191]={de="Alas, my fishing net was carried away by the stream. <Sigh> I'm not too keen to use fishing poles like my friends... If you happen to find my fishing net around, bring it back to me."}
d[71192]={de="Greetings friend! I've been looking for a good place to set up fishing nets around here, but it seems like the population of waddlers around here is too dense - they're eating away most of the juvenile fish before they get a chance to mature. I've made some effigies to scare at least some of those ravenous birds away. This will help us sustain the abundance of fish across the Dragonsprings. Can you help me set those up?"}
d[71193]={de="Did you see that? Underwater! A huge, armored, hungry beast! No way I'm getting near water with my net while that monstrosity lurks below. If you want, you can likely lure it out with a handful of Ominous Conches. Those shouldn't be too hard to catch. To gain conchs, be sure to have your Iskaaran Harpoon handy as you fish in the Dragon Isles."}
d[71194]={de="I found a perfect spot for a fishing net, one problem bothers me though... Those Hornspikes. I'm pretty sure they will ravage the nets as soon as it's left alone. What do we do? ...I've got an idea. We treat our lava fishing nets with Icicle Brew to make them heat-resistant. We just need to teach those hornspikes to keep away from that smell. Toss a flask of Icicle Brew at a hornspike, and then deal some damage to them. Just make sure not to kill them, they won't learn if they're dead, would they?"}
d[71241]={de="The grove called the Primordial Vale is rich with the magic of the old dragons. A type of slyvern there are prized by my kin for their fur, but they are elusive and hard to find. Instead of having you try to track them down, you can find some of our hunting traps in the area. Use meat from the nearby waterfowl to reset them - I will send some of our clan to retrieve whatever gets caught."}
d[72069]={de="The fish could be biting better, don't you think? You know, that gives me an idea. Seems we have caught almost all the fish under the ice. Could you catch some more from the Timbertooth Trail downstream, bring it here, and drop it into an ice hole?"}
d[72072]={de="The fish could be biting better, don't you think? You know, that gives me an idea. Legend says these lakes and rivers did not always have fish. They say, these watering holes were stocked with fish when the dragons soaring overhead dropped them! Can you believe it? Maybe you and your drake could give it a try?"}
d[72074]={de="The fish could be biting better, don't you think? You know, that gives me an idea. Legend says these lakes and rivers did not always have fish. They say, these watering holes were stocked with fish when the dragons soaring overhead dropped them! Can you believe it? Maybe you and your drake could give it a try?"}
d[72075]={de="The fish could be biting better, don't you think? You know, that gives me an idea. Legend says these lava lakes are not always abundant with hot-loving fish. They say, pools were stocked with fish when the dragons soaring overhead dropped them! Can you believe it? Maybe you and your drake could give it a try?"}
d[72384]={de="Fly through the checkpoint rings marking the course."}
d[72586]={de="Keep 'em comin'! The more examples o' furbolg writin' ye collect for me tae cross reference, the better."}
d[72587]={de="Where did ya get that beauty? Tha Primalists seem a lot more interested in destroying civilizations than preserving their history, which makes a find like this all tha more precious. I'll get out me good rubbing stick for this one!"}
