d[73119]={de="Agapanthus says there are more snack orders ready to be retrieved, but we both have our hands full. Would you run out and collect snacks while we tend the whelps?"}
d[73120]={de="Today's activities were interrupted by a spontaneous food fight. This has attracted several undesirable visitors to the daycare! Please help clean up."}
d[73124]={de="The whelps like to spend time with Sir Pringly, but their treading over the space has worn down his habitat. Would you retrieve another shrubbery for him? And while you are out, he could use an adorable new toy. And incense. We cannot let his space fall into disrepair, of course."}
d[73126]={de="Our arts and crafts activities today have gotten well out of hand. One of the whelps enchanted their brush and the rest followed suit. Now there is a coat of paint over everything. Please clean up the daycare while we get the paint off the whelps."}
d[73128]={de="{name}, the whelps are begging us to tell them a story from their favorite anthology, but we are absolutely exhausted. The book the whelps gravitate towards is enchanted and makes every retelling a workout. Would you mind taking over for a spell and tackle story time for us?"}
d[73130]={de="Our magic rune lesson yesterday has apparently bled into today. The whelps are keen on practicing their runes anywhere they can, prudent or not. This fascination has led to an interesting playtime period! Please, help us return the toys to their proper place and dispel any runes you come across."}
d[73131]={de="{name}! I have crafted masterful disguises for me and my friends, but there is only one way to know if they are perfect. Let's play hide and seek! Find us in Valdrakken and I will know my disguises need work!"}
d[73132]={de="Hi, {name}! Do you want to play a game? I have been reading about the greatest hide and seek game in all of Azeroth! I think I can improve on the strategies this book suggests. Let us play a round and test my hypothesis!"}
d[73133]={de="<Posidriss yawns.> I just can't sleep. Let's play a game instead! Maybe there's a comfy hiding spot out there somewhere. I bet you can't find me in the city!"}
d[73134]={de="Ah--ACHOO! Sorry. Do you want to play hide and seek? I found new places to hide and I want to play! I hope my allergies don't stir up any trouble!"}
d[73135]={de="Hi, {name}. <Ruszi looks around nervously.> Do you want to play hide and seek with me? I think it would be very good training. I need to watch out for danger, so it is good to know where to hide. Will you help me practice?"}
d[73192]={de="The trinket appears to be some sort of Noblegarden decoration. It should probably be returned to the festivities in Goldshire."}
d[73226]={de="The fish could be biting better, don't you think? You know, that gives me an idea. Legend says these lakes and rivers did not always have fish. They say, these watering holes were stocked with fish when the dragons soaring overhead dropped them! Can you believe it? Maybe you and your drake could give it a try?"}
d[74117]={de="Rare and dangerous creatures lurk around the creches of the Forbidden Reach. If you and your allies want to stay safe, you should hunt down these threats."}
d[74118]={de="Did you have a chance to visit the Skyfox Den? A very exciting place, from what I've heard. Expedition's spelunkers started surveying the cave and even installed a few grappling hooks on the ceiling, but they were scared away by violent slyverns. Can you do me a favor? Get inside the Skyfox Den, grab the abandoned gear, and check the ceiling for any hidden crevices. Who knows what could be hidden inside?"}
d[74119]={de="Say, have you noticed how good the fishing is around here? Dragonskull Island seems like it would have some great spots to cast a line. Why don't you go there and catch something for dinner? Be mindful, though. We still need to set some of our catch aside for later."}
d[74390]={de="This land is crawling with opportunities for a skilled hunter. We want you to join the hunt. Some threats are feral. Dare I say it, some are greatest threats are sentient and malevolent. If we all work together, we can make the Reach a safe haven, as it used to be."}
d[74391]={de="Say, have you noticed how good the fishing is around here? Dragonskull Island seems like it would have some great spots. Why don't you go there and catch something for dinner? Be mindful, though. We still need to set some of our catch aside for later."}
d[74488]={de="Black whelps have the agility of a rock, but they try to make up for it with the most impressive top speed. Try to take it easy around those corners! [Eruption]: Dash forward. [Rock Halt]: Stops forward movement. [Earthen Will]: Restores all Vigor. Must be grounded."}
d[74489]={de="Bronze whelps can be careless when trying to win, so be careful with the timeways! [Growth Spurt]: Transform into an adult and gain improved speed. [Bedtime Rewind]: Restore 1 Vigor until all Vigor has been recovered. [Sacred Timeline]: Resets cooldowns."}
d[74490]={de="Blue whelps will try to skip ahead where they can, but be careful blinking through rings! [Blink Boost]: Blink forward and dash. [Arcane Acceleration]: Increases forward acceleration. [Accelerated Restoration]: Consumes Arcane Acceleration and restores Vigor."}
d[74491]={de="Green whelps have an affinity for short naps and bursts of speed, so do your best to keep pace. [Nature's Wind]: Fly up then restore 1 Vigor. [Emerald Restraint]: Adds 5 sec to Winds of Life's duration. [Winds of Life]: Anytime you restore Vigor, dash forward."}
d[74492]={de="Red whelps can be a little out of control, so best of luck! [Ruby Exhaustion]: Consumes all Vigor over time. [Crimson Flight]: Restore all Vigor, boosting forward each time. [Renewal]: Consumes Crimson Flight, resets cooldowns."}
d[74514]={de="Has a crowd ever roared for you? Everyone shouting your name, pushing you on to victory? I want to give that same feeling to Slick. Give him the taste of being a champion. Course, we don't speak snail, so we can only be so useful. Round up some snails that could use purpose in their lives. Slick needs a fan club."}
d[74515]={de="Racing snails are all about speed, but riding snails? They need stamina to boot. I owe some supplies to a buddy in Loamm. Why don't you make the delivery for me? Help build Slick's endurance. Oh, and make sure you don't dismount. Not much of a training session if you keep hopping off and on."}
d[74516]={de="It's an off day for our local racing track, so I figured we could take the opportunity to build up Slick's speed. Grow some confidence on his home turf, I'm thinking. Take two laps around the track. Let's see how your training is coming along!"}
d[74517]={de="While life in these caverns is plenty exciting, Slick has a future in the world above. Namely as your trusty mount. Which means he needs to prepare for all sorts of environments. Luckily, the Dragon Isles has biomes to spare. Why don't you take him for a spin? Give him a taste of what's to come. One lap per location should do the trick."}
d[74518]={de="These caverns aren't easy on my poor snails, which is why I feed them a special crystal diet. Keeps their shells hard and gleaming. Slick eats more than his fair share though, so I'm plumb out. Would you collect some crystals in Zaralek Cavern? Get a nice mix, too. We need to make sure Slicks ready for every environment."}
d[74519]={de="Every snail trainer knows that it's all about the goo. The slime. The mucus. That's how you turn a speedy snail into a champion. Slick could use a good slather. Go out and collect some goo from the local slime trails to slick him up. Heh."}
d[74520]={de="Those djaradin think they own these caverns, coming around here and looting our supplies. How am I supposed to train champions under these conditions? Can you do me a favor and get those supplies back? I can't help you train Slick without them. Besides, the big fellow could use a rest day."}
