d[80292]={de="Fly through the checkpoint rings marking the course."}
d[80293]={de="Fly through the checkpoint rings marking the course."}
d[80294]={de="Fly through the checkpoint rings marking the course."}
d[80320]={de="Lend us your aid, Wakener, and the mantid empire will grow."}
d[80426]={de="The Shado-Pan would appreciate any aid you can provide to our cause."}
d[80427]={de="Have you come to aid us?"}
d[80433]={de="To practice is to improve oneself. To give is to improve one's community."}
d[80438]={de="Lok-tar, {name}. What aid do you bring?"}
d[80439]={de="King Varian requests your aid, {name}. Have you any supplies?"}
d[80441]={de="The Cloud Serpents rely on favorable winds. Have you any fortune for us?"}
d[80442]={de="My scouts report enemy activity. Have you any supplies to bring fortune to our troops?"}
d[80443]={de="There will be no victory without bloodshed. Have you brought aid, {class}?"}
d[80444]={de="Hey buddy! Fish up any charms recently? The locals say they bring luck to the waters."}
d[82676]={de="I cannot remember how I arrived at this swamp, but it was great luck that I did. As I wandered, I spotted Lady Katrana Prestor entering a strange toothy cave. Now, what would a noblewoman be doing in such a ghoulish place? Following her closely, I found a great clutch of black dragon eggs within the lair. Such evidence is clear. Katrana is Lady Onyxia! I beg of you, aid me in defeating this vile dragon once and for all."}
d[82689]={de="Long have I waited for this day, hero. Are you and your allies prepared to bring the Lich King to justice? We charge on your command!"}
d[83793]={de="Our people are restless to flow with the waters. Lend aid to our village, that we may move with the currents."}
d[83795]={de="You hozen friend, wikket? Give da jingle jings!"}
d[84222]={de="A veritable menagerie of dangerous creatures have attacked us since we set up our encampment. While my troops can manage most threats, some of the more powerful creatures may require your expertise. Scour the island and eliminate any powerful entities that might jeopardize our operations here."}
d[84432]={de="These Bloodwake vrykul have no regard for us or our research. Even when we tried to share our discoveries with them, we were attacked! They do not care that we mean the isle no harm--they want us to leave. But we cannot leave now. There is so much more to discover! Someone must show them that we're not going to go just yet and that they should leave us alone. We need to show them we will fight back."}
d[84616]={de="Welcome to the Bronze Celebration! We invite you to enjoy our myriad of events. You might choose to mirror your pet and run around our playground. You could participate in one of our big events like Fashion Frenzy or Mount Mania. A different event begins every 15 minutes. Or you might fancy yourself a challenge. If so seek out Chromie as she cleans up her Codex to prepare for her tours. Any event will do, as long as you are having fun!"}
d[84680]={de="The attacking vrykul harness salt and brine elementals, turning them against their foes. To counter their assault, we can harness them as well. Use this Rock Reviver to unleash the elementals residing within nearby stones, transforming them into powerful allies. With their help, we can defeat this vrykul threat."}
d[86486]={de="<The snapdragon seems to recognize you as you approach. Its ear fins wiggle with anticipation. It is hungry again and looks at you expectantly. It seems to want meat and doesn't seem to care where it comes from.>"}
d[87475]={de="Flames! Those chitinous vermin are relentless! We've received reports from Auralia Steelstrike that a small force of nerubians are harassing the outer perimeter of the city. Regroup with our allies on the outskirts of Mereldar and join the fight!"}
d[87477]={de="The Sureki aren't known to give up their assaults so easily. Reports from our southern holdings have warned of a swarm stirring along the mountain range. I don't know whether they plan to hit Tenir's Ascent or Beledar's Bounty, but we cannot wait for them to make the first move. Join our allies and intercept the swarm!"}
d[87480]={de="There's no time to rest, {name}! Our earthen allies in eastern Hallowfall have spotted a Sureki battalion preparing to attack Dunelle's Kindness--they must be targeting the Dawntower! Flame's Radiance reinforcements are securing the town and Lothar's Landing as we speak. Head east and lend what aid you can!"}
d[88711]={de="Our allies in Azj-Kahet have identified a strategic location to strike at the Sureki. According to reports, our enemies are gathering toxins to fuel their war machines. Let's take this opportunity to cut off their supplies, and perhaps better our own understanding of their alchemy."}
d[88916]={de="Credible intel has revealed the Sureki are regrouping for another assault. Now we take the fight to them! The Flame's Radiance have rallied at Faerin's Advance, and prepare to strike at the Sureki forces amassing in northern Azj-Kahet. Be warned, soldier. The Sureki in \"Arathi's End\" are greater in number and power. Should you require aid, our Sacredites in the field should be equipped with potions to assist you."}
d[88945]={de="The nerubian allies you and Lady Faerin made in Azj-Kahet have proven resourceful... for now. According to their intel, Sureki sympathizers have begun to rally at Rak-Zakaz and aid their fallen queen's loyalists in their renewed assaults. Regroup with our forces at Faerin's Advance and cut off their reinforcements!"}
d[89276]={de="Classics are classic for a reason, darling. One simply cannot host a worthwhile soiree without a fine selection of mana for one's guests to indulge in. The Magisters could bring some, but mana is best when freshly siphoned. The mana wyrms in southern Eversong have a decadent brightness to them that I find particularly lovely. Be a dear and gather some for us."}
d[89277]={de="I share our dear Saltheril's love for vintage fixtures, but the lighting enchantment he is using is far too common for such an auspicious occasion. My Magisters can create a far more stunning enchantment. Simply gather some fibers from the Lightbloom for me and I can have them broken down into spell reagents. The effect will be marvelous."}
d[89278]={de="While the court does demand our consideration, we cannot forget duties. Our guests will enjoy themselves more freely if they are assured of the solidity of Eversong's defenses. The Magisters are tasked with maintaining the runestone wards throughout Eversong. Please survey them for us and let us know if any wards need our attention."}
d[91971]={de="The Twilight Hammer is dirtying up the ruins of Zeb'tala. Clean up the area and bring back some of their personal tokens. One never knows what curiosities may appeal to those vying for relevancy. Those mindless cultists may stomp around and act tough, but you will make quick work of them."}
d[91972]={de="There is still a lot of friction on the border with Zul'Aman, but we must hold the watch on all fronts. Check in with Bloodguard Nelric at the Thalassian Pass. It is rumored to be one of the most uneventful posts. I am certain he would appreciate a reprieve, if only for a few moments. Stay alert, {name}!"}
d[91973]={de="It seems the locals currently find great appeal in naga blades--the brinier the better. On our southwestern shore, you will find the Daggerspine naga. They have these grungy, barnacle-encrusted scimitars that would perfectly fit the bill. Go grab a few of those. They could have value in some of our upcoming discussions."}
d[91974]={de="I guess there is one benefit to being part of the courtly intrigue: one does hear things. We have this concoction of sunfire infused with the holy energy of the Blood Knights, courtesy of the court alchemists. Take this down to the Sanctum of the Moon and test it on the Twilight intruders. I look forward to hearing the results in detail."}
d[91975]={de="It seems the lure of the lightwood continues to be a problem. We may as well take advantage of the trolls' hard work! Collect what they have harvested. We can make use of it. What we do not use for weapons, we can hand over to the carvers. The nobles will clamor over lightwood decor."}
d[91976]={de="All of this small talk makes my ears twitch. I would be so much more useful doing field work. For now, you get to do the fun part. The creatures within the Lightbloom are getting a bit dense. I need you to get out there and lower the volume. I am sure you'll run into many options while you are out there. Take a whack at a few for me."}
d[91977]={de="The Tideborne are always running just over the legal line. They are an annoyance at best, but will push boundaries when given too much rope. The ones in Sunsail Anchorage made the mistake of ripping off some nobles not too long ago. Maybe go smack them around a bit--remind them to respect their betters."}
d[91978]={de="Have you ever noticed, that sometimes there is benefit in letting someone think they are getting away with something? The Tideborne will continue to smuggle in plain sight, feeling clever at the taxes they're avoiding paying to Silvermoon. This does add up, though, over time. When you have a moment, please head down to the harbor and relieve them of some of their back taxes."}
d[91979]={de="We received word there's a creature from Lightbloom Ath'Ran making trouble on the western coast. It has caused a bit of drama. Head over and resolve the issue."}
d[91983]={de="The beautiful members of the Silvermoon Court do so love their colorful embellishments. For this, we can stock up while doing a good deed! Head over to Thuron's Livery and pick up some of the brightly colored feathers shed from the hawkstriders in training. Vaelith gets clean up service and we get the lovely plumage."}
d[91984]={de="Oh, {name}, have you ever visited the Solaarian Sunbath? If not, it's highly recommended. The sungrubs that wander nearby have a precious silk from which amazing fabric can be made. Solwin Brightstitch is reputed to be masterful in this, with his sartorial magic. The raw materials are often sought out to have him create unique and personalized goods from scratch. Bring us some of that lovely silk. It will provide a soft cushion when faced with harder discussions."}
d[91985]={de="The nobles do so love the unusual. Take a look around Windrunner Village. There are sure to be some interesting mementos still tucked away there. I will find an advantageous home for the pieces you bring back."}
d[91986]={de="Those naga are, as ever, being a beachfront nuisance. Do they not understand that is a prime location? We may not be able to reliably drive them off, but a little mischief would not be untoward. I found this tune that drives the snapdragons mad. They will just attack whoever is nearby. Take this and give it a shot!"}
d[91987]={de="It seems some of the nobles are botany-curious where the Lightbloom is concerned. They seek the exotic to adorn their windowsills and lurk in the dangerous section of their greenhouses. That's where you come in, {name}! Go harvest those small and pernicious plants. Their bulbs will be the best for planting."}
d[91988]={de="The conservators at Brightwing Estate have a mischievous young dragonhawk named Cerul that likes to run away whenever their backs are turned. He doesn't go far, but it has become a game for him to get them to chase him. Take this delicious treat with you and use it to lure him back home."}
d[91989]={de="The delicate blue ghostland peppers may not look like much, but they have a mean burn. Many nobles won't admit it, but they are quite popular in the noble games of \"Truth or Challenge.\" Please procure a few for me. I like to watch them sweat."}
d[91990]={de="Naga have set up camp on the Sunset Strand. The sunset slugs that called it home are distraught and seem unsure what to do. This little tune will remind them of their home. Go inspire them to seek the freedom of the open sea."}
d[91991]={de="When conversations get tense, it can be challenging to keep words flowing in a productive way. At times like these, I find a little social lubrication is in order. Swing over to Goldenmist Village and pick up a cask of Vintner's Golden. It's proven to have a euphoric side effect that can be quite helpful."}
d[91992]={de="I entrusted one of my apprentices with the delivery of several cases of particularly expensive wine. He was to bring them here from my private storage, but he has not yet arrived. I should hate to ask you to retrieve him, but I cannot stress enough how expensive those bottles are. Please see if you can locate him and my delivery. He should have been traveling from the north to arrive here."}
d[91993]={de="Keeping preciously small animals as pets is a popular pastime among the nobility. The more unconventional the animal, often obtained through magic, the more of a conversation piece it is. I have enchanted this wand with the appropriate shrinking spell. Use it on some of the colorful toads out near the ponds and bring them back here. The nobles will find them delightful. Naturally, the toads may not take kindly to the enchantment. But I trust you can handle that, should it occur."}
d[91994]={de="Lord Saltheril, that old lynx, has put me in a bit of a bind. He has requested a grand fireworks display to accompany tonight's dinner service, but we are dreadfully low on pyrepetal dust. It is an herb native to Eversong, highly flammable and quite dazzling when set aflame by pyromancy. Could you help us replenish our stores? We mostly harvest it from the woods near Scintilas Falls."}
d[91995]={de="Have you seen the encampments the naga have been constructing along our coast? Dreadful business. Not only do they menace our ships and disrupt our trade routes, but they might pose a real threat to Eversong's inland settlements if allowed to continue operations unchecked. Their arcanists are particularly dangerous. Dispose of them and our guests will be in your debt."}
d[91996]={de="Battle prowess and magical skill are important, of course, but one cannot deny the power of appearances. A well-dressed army instills far more faith than one bedecked in rags. Fortunately, a fine set of robes can be both flattering and functional. The mana silk produced at the North Sanctum can be woven into robes that deepen and intensify our magical reserves. Be a dear and gather some for us, would you? My wardrobe could use a seasonal refreshment."}
d[91997]={de="The festivities have been wonderfully entertaining, which means the nobles have been leaving a bit of a mess around the estate. Lord Saltheril's servants have been keeping up with the cleaning, but the Magisters could lend a hand. Enchanting a few brooms to sweep the pavilion should be an easy but impressive feat. I was informed that an arcanist was employing the same tactic over at Farstrider Hold. Go retrieve some of his brooms and I will have them re-enchanted here."}
d[91999]={de="You know, I bring Saltheril a lot of \"imported\" wine, but one of the first things I started supplying him with was bloodthistle. It's an herb that only grows around Eversong. It's got a smooth bite to it, sort of like mana. Nice and classy. His parties really go through the stuff. I took a look and I don't think he has enough to last this whole thing. We should get some more. The best stuff grows over by the West Sanctum. Grab as much as you can carry. Trust me--it'll go fast."}
d[92000]={de="This place is pretty fun so far, despite all the dry political talk. I know Saltheril is trying to get the nobles to buy up war bonds, but we could really use some more energy in here. If the nobles are all asleep, no one's buying anything. Tell you what. Go invite some of my friends. They hang out under the bridge right outside of Silvermoon's gates. If anyone can bring some energy to the soiree, it's us."}
d[92001]={de="The whole point of this deal is showing the nobles what we bring to the table, both for Silvermoon and for them personally. These other groups bring strength, power, and really nice armor. What we bring is resources: getting the sin'dorei what they need, when they need it, with no questions asked. I heard some folks over at Sunsail Anchorage have been trying out the same business, but they're putting gold in the wrong pockets. Swipe their stock and bring it here."}
d[92002]={de="You'd be surprised at the money you can make off of weapons. No, not the kind you're meant to use--the kind you stick up on the wall and have conversations about. Usually those weapons are expensive, or dangerous, or otherwise hard to get your hands on. The more rare and exclusive, the better. The weapons those Twilight cultists are carrying around should sell pretty well, especially to buyers with edgier tastes. If you happen to come across any, I'll gladly take them off your hands."}
d[92003]={de="Don't let the austere demeanor fool you. Nobles are just as susceptible to flashy party favors as the rest of us. I had my people bring over a batch of Felo'melorn replicas. They look great on display, and even better--they're enchanted. Swing them around and they leave a trail of fire. I haven't sold an enchanted batch before, so I'd like to do some testing before I hand them out. Saltheril wouldn't be too happy if I burned a guest to a crisp. Wanna take one of the replicas for a test run?"}
d[92004]={de="I feel like I just got here and I'm already fresh out of half the poisons I brought. What? Don't look at me like that. Nobles are some of my top customers for poisons. Quieter than magic and cleaner than blades. I need to restock. The frogs way down in the south produce a poisonous slime that I can bottle without much fuss. Bring some of it to me and I'll get you a cut of the earnings."}
d[92005]={de="We've been making friends with some of the guests by teaching them how to play dice. It's a nice way to draw people out of the crowd and get them in a quieter space where you can talk privately. I wasn't expecting so much interest, to be honest. We're running out of dice sets. I can carve some more, but I'll need materials. Usually teeth or bone are good picks. Actually, the fangs from those naga along the coast would be perfect. Now that's a conversation starter!"}
d[92006]={de="I talked to some of the servants earlier and it sounds like the casks are running low. That's a recipe for disaster at an event like this. Fortunately, I've got a lot of contacts across Eversong who can help us restock. I need to stay here and play politics, but could you head over to Tranquillien and grab a few bottles? I'll give you a list."}
d[92007]={de="The oldest trick in the book is to create a problem on purpose, solve it yourself, and look like the hero. One of the nobles just got word that some prized valuable was stolen from their estate while they were occupied here. It just so happens I might have put one of their servants up to it. Go talk to a man named Seridis over at the livery. He'll hand over the valuable to you, then you'll come back here and pretend you valiantly subdued the thief and retrieved the item. Everyone's happy."}

-- Hand-added 2026-06-19: descriptions backfilled from warcraft.wiki.gg (CC BY-SA) / Wowhead
-- for tracked quests the Blizzard /quest API returned no description for.
d[11354]={de="Today I have a buyer who is interested in a piece that's held by the mount of Illidan's herald.  I, of course, speak of Vazruden the Herald and his dragon mount, Nazan. If you want the finder's fee that I offer in return, find them flying above the Ramparts at Hellfire Citadel and return with the dragon's riding crop. My sources tell me that the item in question is personally held by the dragon.  It is said Nazan refuses to allow Vazruden to strike him with it."}
d[11362]={de="There is no accounting for taste. Take my most recent buyer for instance. There is a blood orc within Hellfire Citadel known as Keli'dan the Breaker. He bears a most mundane stave; certainly nothing to take a second glance at. And yet, this is what my customer wishes. Who am I to say no? If you desire my compensation, you will find him and his stave within the Blood Furnace."}
d[11363]={de="Today I have a very wealthy collector in need of something very unique indeed. Warchief Kargath Bladefist carries upon his person his seal of command, which he uses to sign all official documents. I want you to retrieve it for me. You will find him deep within the Shattered Halls. No doubt you will have to wade through a veritable army to get to him. I have no doubt that you will succeed."}
d[11364]={de="Do you question your master?  Neither does Mah'duun. The blood of the centurions of the Shattered Hand clan is what I seek.  You will find them within the Shattered Halls of Hellfire Citadel. If you want the bounty, you will not return until you have slain them all."}
d[11368]={de="I have an unusual request.  A certain wealthy individual that I am in contact with off-world is interested in a macabre piece.  Specifically, she wants the heart of Quagmirran. I hear that the beast has three, but one will suffice for our purposes.  As I understand it, you can find Quagmirran resting within a deep pool of water at the Slave Pens."}
d[11370]={de="While it is known that Warlord Kalithresh of the naga is a great warrior in his own right, there are fewer who know that he has codified all of his knowledge. One of my customers is aware of it though, and is keenly interested in obtaining his treatise. I ask that you travel to the Steamvault in Coilfang Reservoir and obtain this book for me."}
d[11371]={de="Mah'duun hears and obeys, and I now ask you to be my instrument. It has been related to me that the myrmidons of the coilfang tribe must be destroyed. Seek them out within the humid confines of the Steamvault underneath Coilfang Reservoir. I will accept nothing less than their utter annihilation."}
d[11372]={de="I've recently been approached by a tauren whose husband is about to be elevated to chieftain. She wishes to make a special addition to his headdress. Specifically, she wants to obtain the headfeathers from the dastardly Talon King Ikiss. If you are interested in collecting my reward, travel to Auchindoun's Sethekk Halls and find him."}
d[11373]={de="Today I have a personal request of you, yet the reward will certainly match the danger. My family has a 'history', shall we say, with Nexus-Prince Shaffar and his followers. If the amulet he wears were to fall into my hands then surely that would mean that he had been dealt with. If the bounty I am offering is of interest to you then journey to his lair within Auchindoun's Mana-Tombs."}
d[11374]={de="Within Auchindoun's Auchenai Crypts many unsavory experiments are undertaken in the pursuit of a greater understanding of the necromantic arts. Many are the spirits that are tortured or destroyed therein. I have a customer who is interested in the liberation of one of those spirits. I have been informed that this spirit is contained within a soul gem held by none other than Exarch Maladaar himself. Seek him out within the crypts with all due haste and return to me with the gem."}
d[11375]={de="When I'm done speaking, you may not want to take this commission. I have an eccentric client who specializes in the study of dead realities.  It is rumored that the being known as Murmur destroyed the last world from which he was summoned.  The professor is interested in examining his 'whisper' as he called it to understand how it is that Murmur accomplished such a feat. Will you journey to the Shadow Labyrinth within Auchindoun and retrieve it for me?"}
d[11376]={de="Mah'duun has heard it said that none are as cruel as the six-armed demonesses inside the Shadow Labyrinth. Go to Auchindoun, seek them out, kill them all. If you cannot accomplish so simple a task, we do not have anything further to say to one another."}
d[11378]={de="The tastes of my customers range from the mundane to the exotic. And sometimes they want to do very mundane things with the exotic objects they seek. Such is the case with my latest request. My client, who shall remain nameless, wishes to obtain the head of the Epoch Hunter to mount on his wall. <Class>, will you find a way to travel back in time to Old Hillsbrad and procure said head for my trophy-hunting patron?"}
d[11382]={de="I swear that some of my customers are crazy.  There are possessions that you go after, and there are ones that you dare not even think of! My current client is clearly over-the-top insane.  He covets the hourglass that Aeonus holds. Yes, you heard right, Aeonus of the Infinite Dragonflight! Who am I to argue since he's paying a king's ransom? So, ready to go to the Caverns of Time and travel to the Black Morass to retrieve it for me?"}
d[11383]={de="Mah'duun knows where you must go.  Mah'duun knows that you must kill rift lords. But, Mah'duun does not know exactly when. I know that does not make sense, but the voice on the winds was not more specific. Travel to the Black Morass through the Caverns of Time and the way shall be made clear."}
d[11384]={de="Not long ago, I was approached by a kaldorei druidess with a touching request. And plenty of gold, of course! It would appear that the forces of Darnassus wish to restore an ancient of the arcane known as Warp Splinter. The giant tree has been confused or corrupted, I'm not certain, but you'll find it inside of the Botanica at Tempest Keep. She said that all they would need to regrow him was a small clipping."}
d[11385]={de="It has been whispered to Mah'duun that the channelers of the military unit known as the Sunseekers must be killed today. They are to be found within the Botanica at Tempest Keep. You want the bounty, you kill the channelers."}
d[11386]={de="I always assumed that Pathaleon the Calculator used magic to project his image across Outland.  Apparently I was wrong. My latest customer tells me that the blood elf uses a mechanical device for his communication with the leaders of Prince Kael'thas's special projects.  As I understand it, he acquired it from the Zaxxis rebels in the Netherstorm. My client wishes to obtain the projector.  Why don't you pay Pathaleon a visit? He can be found within the Mechanar at Tempest Keep."}
d[11387]={de="There are mechanical constructs within the Mechanar which Mah'duun has been told must be dismantled. Go to Tempest Keep, find the tempest-forge destroyers and destroy them. Then you may return to collect the bounty."}
d[11388]={de="Today's client seeks something truly unique. It is said that Harbinger Skyriss is a servant of the Old Gods.  It is also said that he carries a large scroll that contains their instructions for his domination of life in the universe on their behalf. My current buyer wishes to get his hands on that scroll, nevermind that he won't be able to read the language upon it. Travel to Tempest Keep's Arcatraz and get it for me, will you, <class>?"}
d[11389]={de="The sentinels within the Arcatraz have gone haywire. The prisoners run rampant and the guards attack those that would help. Mah'duun hears the speaker on the nether winds. The speaker says to destroy the sentinels. Accomplish this and today's bounty is yours."}
d[11499]={de="<Class>, today I ask the impossible. Today, you must obtain the signet ring of Kael'thas Sunstrider, lord of the blood elves! It's true, the rumors of his death within Tempest Keep were ill-founded. He has appeared once more, this time at the Magisters' Terrace on the Isle of Quel'Danas. What he is doing there is a tale for someone else to tell you. What I know is that I have innumerable collectors interested in his princely ring, and I mean to acquire it for them. Or rather, I mean for you to do so."}
d[11500]={de="It has been whispered to Mah'duun that the sisters of torment are to be sent back to the hells from which they sprang. Mah'duun knows that these demons can be found at the Magisters' Terrace on the Isle of Quel'Danas. You will do this thing to earn the bounty, or you will not."}
d[11525]={de="My plan to replace the damaged crystals on the erratic sentries has been a success. We've managed to take the Sun's Reach Sanctum with their help. I've crafted new crystals that will bring more of them under our control; place them inside the hulls of defeated sentries. We'll deploy them to other locations once they've been converted."}
d[11533]={de="We've taken the armory from the enemy thanks to our aerial attacks against the Legion's forces in the Dead Scar. As a matter of fact, it's gone so well that we're going to continue our air strikes against them. Take these arcane charges and use them against their forces. Talk to Ayren Cloudbreaker at the Shattered Sun Staging Area when you're ready for flight."}
d[11536]={de="Now that we have an anvil, I can really get to work. No matter how many supplies we receive, I'll always be able to put the Darkspine Iron Ore to good use. We'll need a constant supply of weapons and armor if we're to be successful here. There are a group of naga on the coast to the east of here. They're collecting ore and placing it in chests for shipment to the Legion. Relieving them of their ore will help our efforts in more ways than one...."}
d[11540]={de="We've driven the Dawnblade army out of the Sun's Reach Harbor. Sun's Reach is ours in its entirety. Yet somehow... I'm not entirely satisfied. I want you to go to Dawnstar Village, west of here, and slay any surviving Dawnblade combatants. They sealed their fate when they followed Kael to this place."}
d[11541]={de="The naga have taken the Greengill Coast to the southeast. Their females, the Darkspine sirens, are using magic to enslave the indigenous murlocs. It's my responsibility to see to it that whatever the naga are up to over there is disrupted. That's where you come in. <class>, I want you to get the controlling orbs from the female naga and throw them near the Greengill slaves, breaking the orb and setting the murlocs free. My guess is that the murlocs will be incensed and turn on their masters."}
d[11543]={de="We've managed to capture Sun's Reach in its entirety. Unfortunately a fleet of Dawnblade reservists is on its way to take back the harbor. Take this oil and secure a dragonhawk from Ayren Cloudbreaker. You should be able to fly within reach of the ships' sails; once you're close enough, set them on fire. Land in one of the ships and attack the reservists. With their ship sails on fire they won't be able to mount much of a defense."}
d[11544]={de="The Ata'mal Terrace in eastern Shadowmoon Valley is holy to the draenei, but is now overrun by fel orcs. They have dug up the special ore from that place and created corrupted weapons and armor. I need the armaments to form an alloy with the naga ore. Our anchorites have blessed my anvil with the ability to cleanse them. Retrieve the armaments from the Shadowmoon chosen, slayers and darkweavers. Return them here, breaking down and purifying them upon my anvil, and then hand me the cleansed results."}
d[11546]={de="Welcome, <name>. There are a number of ways I can assist you in your efforts here. For example, I've recently discovered a recipe for a unique elixir. The bloodberry grows wild in many regions of Azeroth and has long been considered nothing more than a nuisance. I've learned though, that when exposed to the Sunwell's power this plant takes on special properties that can be distilled and imbibed to magnify one's abilities. Bring me a sample from the nearby bushes and I'll show you what I mean."}
d[11547]={de="Freeloaders! You all want instant gratification - never giving thought to the effort required to create even the simplest of portals. Perhaps a little education will instill a bit of gratitude for my ceaseless efforts. Take this crystal. Attune it to the Bloodcrystal to the west, at the Dawning Square portal just south of here, and at the naga shrine at Greengill Coast to the southeast. Perhaps then you'll appreciate your precious translocations...."}
d[11665]={de="Hello <lad/lass>. I'm glad you've stopped by to talk to this old man — there's trouble back home. A traveling merchant recently sold a batch of baby crocolisks to some gullible children. Crocolisks are wild beasts, and many have escaped and now lurk in city waterways. Grab your strongest fishing pole and drop a line in Stormwind or Orgrimmar and bring one of the little devils back to me. I'm anxious to see one."}
d[11668]={de="There's a lot of big fish in the Zangarmarsh lakes. Ever wonder what they eat? Shrimp. Giant freshwater shrimp."}
d[11669]={de="This old man is going hunting soon. I'm gonna take down a mammoth shark off the coast of Azshara. The thing is, I need a toxin that'll stay on a spear tip while it's underwater. To make that kind of stuff, I need the glands from a poisonous fish: the felblood snapper. Such a vile fish only thrives in the horrific waters of Hellfire Peninsula and Shadowmoon Valley. Bring me back a whopper and I'll be a happy old man."}
d[11880]={de="I'm sure that 'gnomish inventor' is a crackpot. He was babbling about some red clouds that have begun to appear in the Spirit Fields around Oshu'gun in Nagrand."}
d[13103]={de="Ranid Glowergold in the Leatherworkers shop in Dalaran has had a sudden craving for wine and cheese."}
d[13114]={de="We be havin' another order to fill. Da innkeeper in da Dalaran sewers needs a vegetable stew as his customers they don't have so much to eat, mon."}
d[13592]={de="The tournament is a time for testing your skills against your peers, but we must not forget that the real enemy, the Scourge, will not wait."}
d[13665]={de="The grand melee is the most important of the tournament's competitions. The people of Stormwind adore their knights and are looking forward to seeing us win the melee. To that end, they've been honing their skills against the other valiants. I suggest you do the same. Go to the stables outside the pavilion, equip your lance, mount the stabled Elwynn steed, and challenge the valiants. They wait in the Alliance Valiants' Ring just outside our tent."}
d[13682]={de="Highlord Tirion Fordring has doubled the guard since your exposure of the Cult of the Damned's infiltrator. He doesn't believe that they will stop just because their Black Knight has been defeated. Our skytalon scouts have reported sighting a frost wyrm named Chillmaw leading a cult raiding party. If we don't intercept them, the tournament will come under attack. The scouts reporting seeing Chillmaw to the southwest, flying over the area between the Ironwall Rampart and Aldur'thar."}
d[13789]={de="The coliseum is perched in the most dangerous part of the world, <name>. The territory we've taken from the Scourge has been paid for in blood and misery, yet the enemy continues to strike back with a seemingly limitless army. To make matters worse, this undead army is supported and assisted by mortal sympathizers, the Cult of the Damned. Go forth into Icecrown and slay any cultists you encounter."}
d[13790]={de="As a champion, you have mastered the art of mounted combat, besting challengers of all levels. When the tournament begins, those you have defeated will have redoubled their efforts and will seek to avenge their losses to you. It would be wise to continue practicing your skills against the combatants waiting in the Ring of Champions. Equip your lance, go to the stables on the southern side of the grounds. then mount up on any mount you're permitted to use, and face the champions."}
d[13847]={de="Even as we ready for the tournament, Argent Crusade forces prepare the way for an assault on the enemy's stronghold of Icecrown Citadel. In the Court of Bones in southwestern Icecrown, a few brave crusaders have set up a forward camp on the southern side of Corp'rethar. Equip your lance and mount the stabled campaign charger at the camp, then destroy the Lich King's minions. Do not fear the masses of boneguard footmen, <name>, for they can easily be trampled under your horse's hooves."}
d[13861]={de="Even as some of us labor on the tournament, our brothers prepare the way for an assault on the enemy's stronghold of Icecrown Citadel."}
d[14048]={de="I've been cooking nonstop since before the start of the holiday, and I still can't keep up with the demand. I don't suppose I could persuade you to help with one of the dishes, could I?"}
d[14051]={de="Keeping these tables stocked can be overwhelming! I've got to make the cranberry chutney while keeping my eye on the sweet potatoes, and making sure the pies don't burn. I think I've got everything covered. No, wait, I'm forgetting something. The stuffing! Oh, no. There won't be time to get another batch of stuffing started before everything else is done. Would you be willing to help me out? It shouldn't take long to buy or make some stuffing and you can buy the ingredients right here."}
d[14053]={de="My husband, Jasper, was going to make more cranberry chutney, but it looks like he's busy trying to make sure there's enough candied sweet potatoes for all the guests. Would you be willing to help? If you're a cook, you can get the tangy Wetlands cranberries you'll need from the Pilgrim's Bounty vendor outside Ironforge. If you don't feel up to cooking, you could always ask someone else to make the chutney, too."}
d[14054]={de="Isaac's been hard at work helping celebrants learn about the traditional Pilgrim's Bounty feast and how to make dishes out of all the ingredients we harvest at this time of year. I've been trying to keep the tables stocked with as many of the dishes as I can, but we're running out of one of Isaac's favorites, pumpkin pie. Would you be able to get some for us? If you want to make the pies yourself, you'll need to buy ripe Elwynn pumpkins from the Pilgrim's Bounty vendor outside Stormwind."}
d[14055]={de="My wife Ellen has enlisted my help in keeping the tables stocked, but she can't make up her mind. First I was making pumpkin pie, but now she's changed her mind and she wants candied sweet potatoes. Well, I've already started on the pie, so maybe you can help me whip up those sweet potatoes. She'll be pleasantly surprised if we can get everything she's asked for. If you're going to cook the sweet potatoes yourself, you'll have to buy them from the Pilgrim's Bounty merchant in Darnassus. Thanks, <name>."}
d[14105]={de="The Cult of the Damned has redoubled its efforts to see us destroyed. They have grown bold and are massing their strength at Deathspeaker's Watch on the ridge west of the tournament grounds. The ruthless Deathspeaker Kharos has his men fortifying their positions, preparing to unleash all of the cult's weapons. My men are preparing themselves and the valiants to defend the grounds, but I want champions like you, <name>, to lead our efforts to blunt the attack. Find Deathspeaker Kharos and slay him."}
d[26094]={de="My chief engineer tells me that he's managed to get one of the bombers repaired and airworthy. Take these bombs with you, and look for the repaired bomber at the start of the runway. Once you're airborne, use the bombs to do as much damage to the attacking Dark Iron dwarves as you can. I've heard rumors that they're preparing to deploy a new kind of war golem. Keep your eyes peeled for those golems and make them your highest priority targets."}
d[26153]={de="My daughter Penny loves pumpkin pancakes but we have had a shortage of pumpkins here in Elwynn from the frostbite last season. I have heard of a new pumpkin patch north of Stormwind that might be ripe for the picking now though. Head out and harvest a few of those ripe pumpkins for me and let's see what we can do."}
d[26414]={de="Sometimes, I fish for fun. Other times to relax, but sometimes I want a challenge. That's where the hardened walleye comes into the picture. This prized fish is not caught for us to eat, but for the challenge. You can find the walleye in Stormwind Lake just north of the city. Think you are up to the challenge?"}
d[26420]={de="Hey there, Angler! Arnold here tells me that you have been looking for a new fishing spot and I think I know just the place. North of Stormwind there is a great little spot called Olivia's Pond. The pond is stocked with crystal bass every year but they are hard to catch. They only bite on a very specific type of bait... overgrown earthworms. If you search the shore around the pond, you should find plenty of worms to use as bait."}
d[26442]={de="If I could choose my last meal, it would definitely be fresh lobster tail. Something about that tasty crustacean is just irresistible! We recently started trapping lobsters here in Stormwind. Would you mind heading out and checking the traps for me? One more thing, watch out for the sharks. They can be vicious down there."}
d[26488]={de="Arnold and I used to relax down at the moat in the Valley of Heroes. One day, I lost my locket in the lake and I have never been able to find it. Rumor has it that huge royal monkfish live in that moat and that they eat anything! I know it's a long shot, but do you think you could catch a few monkfish and look for my locket? Please let me know right away if you find it, it's very precious to me."}
d[26536]={de="Arnold and I have been fishing in and around Stormwind for years now. That's the kind of time it takes to find a good fishing spot. One of my favorites is called Thunder Falls. It's just south of Stormwind in Elwynn Forest. Best part about Thunder Falls is the violet perch. I have never seen them anywhere else, only up there at the falls. It's a bit of hike for me and Arnold to get out there these days though, do you think you could head up there and fetch some of those perch for us?"}
d[28689]={de="Many soldiers died on this island <name>. It is only fair that we pay our respects to them in any way that we can. I need you to travel to Forgotten Hill, due west of here and release our brothers in arms' tortured souls away from this place. Do be careful over there, reports of undead have been ongoing in the area."}
d[28751]={de="Even though we beat Warden Stillwater, his zombies still roam the countryside. Look there, another wave is approaching! Help me fight them off, old buddy! Let's go!"}
d[29192]={de="We must tread carefully, <class>. Fandral's Druids of the Flame practice their fiery magic beyond the pillars to the north. I need you to capture one of those druids alive for questioning. We must seize every opportunity to learn of their plans. One of my wardens will accompany you. Follow her instructions if you wish to survive."}
d[29257]={de="We've discovered a new species of flower growing in the Magma Springs to the north. Amazingly, they sustain themselves in pure molten lava! Please go and retrieve some specimens for me. I'm sure that further study of these plants will shed some light on your little friend here. Speaking of which, he seems quite eager to go with you. Let's hope he behaves himself."}
d[29289]={de="Unsurprisingly, their matriarch has taken offense to us taking her young to train for our own uses. It's understandable... and a bit tragic actually. We are very much the villains in this exchange. Now is not the time for such thoughts. These creatures are beings of fire, and on more than one occasion, they've claimed the lives of our kin. With their matriarch angered, the danger has grown immensely. I need someone to quiet her rage, and I fear you may be the most capable."}
d[29290]={de="Look at that! It's incredible! Born less than two days ago and already full grown. Sadly, I suspect their life cycle is similarly short, so we'll have to take advantage of any time we have. His training went remarkably well. I want you to be the one to take him out and unleash him on the bulk of the enemy forces gathered near Ragnaros' keep. Show no mercy, <race>."}
d[29296]={de="The fire hawks are upset by our continued presence. They're getting extremely hostile, and not just in the usual territorial ways. I worry that if we leave them unchecked, they will soon be joining the assault on our tree, and I'm not sure we're capable of handling that. Go across the way to Fireplume Peak and do what you have to to keep them in check. I'm far more concerned with our safety right now than theirs, so be decisive about it."}
d[29364]={de="One of Thunder Bluff's most important staples is cornmeal; bowls of corn may be found in nearly every home. With so many of the local mills under constant attack by harpies, gnolls, reckless mining companies and Earth Mother knows what else, I often ask my students to help with the task of grinding corn into cornmeal. Would you care to help?"}
d[29438]={de="Think you're a good shot? Quick on the trigger? It'll cost you just a single game token to test your skills. What do you say? How good are you?"}
d[29455]={de="Hey there! Step right up! Why not show everyone how skilled you are? Just land three rings on the Darkmoon Turtle and you'll get a prize. For one game token you can buy a stack of rings and show the world why we call you the 'Eagle Eyed <class>.'"}
d[29463]={de="So you want to whack some gnolls? Well you've come to the right place. Your goal is simple, score 30 points in a minute. Use the mallet I give you and get ready to whack. Speak to me when you are ready to start."}
d[31118]={de="We need to understand what went wrong with the Deadtalkers. For so many years, the Deadtalkers were simply responsible for maintaining the burial grounds and holding funerals for fallen warriors. From a recent raid, we've recovered a tablet from the grounds that is clearly written using a cipher, but it isn't one we've encountered before. If you can gather a ciphered scroll from one of the Deadtalkers, we can begin to put together the cypher and understand what's happened."}
d[31444]={de="You have fished up something special. It looks pretty aggressive. Maybe Nat Pagle at the Anglers Wharf might know more about it?"}
d[33146]={de="Hello, <name>. Care to work the noodle stand again? Just let me know when you're ready to work another shift and I'll get everything set up."}
d[33358]={de="Hello, <name>. Think you're a truly extraordinary noodle chef? Let's see what you've got!"}
d[35073]={de="We need to stock the garrison pond with local fish. I need you to search the waters in Shadowmoon Valley for fish that we can stock up with. Once you have the fish, you will need to slice them up and look for eggs inside."}
d[74389]={de="The arthropods in Caldera of the Menders are truly vicious. One of our gyrocopters went missing there! Our expedition sent a unmanned surveillance aircraft there, but it hasn't returned. Can you find the gyrocopter? You could use it to capture the Caldera's wildlife on camera?"}

d[12582]={de="I know you weren't traitor thing like others said. We hunt together... I know you better than all of them. Thank you for saving me. May sound funny... I not a big fan of big-tongues... but even I feel little bad for big-tongue dying like that though...they fight good enough they deserve fair fight. You want to be friends with Frenzyheart again? I think I can convince them that you save me and got the big-tongues good. I no want you to make me look dumb though, so you sure no more big-tongues for you?"}
d[12689]={de="Hi! Really glad see you again! I knew we friends. I knew it! You good friend. Not just for us, but for all Oracles. Thank you for saving us! Thank you, thank you! I saw you bonk that puppy-man good! Undead thing said he your friend before? I not know that. You done with puppy-men though, yeah? Just Oracle friend now? Stop! No agree without thinking - you sure you not want to be friends with puppy-men anymore?"}
d[31752]={de="I am pleased to offer this gift to you, <race> <class>.  According to my calibrations, it will invoke feelings of enjoyment and gratitude. Have a nice day."}
d[32304]={de="Your presence on the battlefield cannot be ignored. I would like to give you something extra for your efforts, <class>."}
d[32631]={de="Your presence on the battlefield cannot be ignored. I would like to give you something extra for your efforts, <class>."}
d[46049]={de="<Your tadpole has prepared a gift for you. What could be inside?>"}
d[56042]={de="OUTPUT: Please accept this GIFT. ADMINISTER GIFT DISTRIBUTION PROTOCOL."}
d[56322]={de="Talk to Brewmaster Tsing in the Brewfest grounds."}
d[56714]={de="Talk to Brewmaster Tao in the Brewfest grounds."}
d[77897]={de="Well, if it isn't my trusty investigator. There's a contact in the Kirin Tor who owes me a favor. They gave me a tip about a book in Karazhan that might help us decipher those tablets you recovered. You know, the ones from the Azure Span and Shifting Sands? But we both know you're the one with the securing skills here. Here's the note my contact left. Should help you find the book!"}
d[92855]={de="What, you think I'm just going to give you my crafts for free? <Lidamorrutu grumbles.> I suppose that's exactly what I'm going to do. Eternus's orders, something about speeding up the experiment. Just don't lose it or, worse, let Erus anywhere near it."}
